{"title_page": "Arne Birkenstock", "text_new": "{{short description|German film director and screenwriter|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n'''Arne Birkenstock''' (born 1967) is a German [[film director]] and [[screenwriter]].\n\n==History==\nArne Birkenstock was born in Huettental, [[Germany]] and was raised in [[Cologne]], [[Germany]]. Birkenstock studied [[economy]], [[political Science]], [[History of Latin America]] and [[Romance Languages]] in [[Cologne]], [[Germany]], [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]] and [[C\u00f3rdoba, Argentina|C\u00f3rdoba]], [[Argentina]] and received a [[Master's degree]] in [[Latin American Studies]].{{citation needed|date=October 2012}}\n\nBirkenstock published several studies and non-fiction books on Latin American music and on arts and media policy for German publishing houses and governmental institutions. He has written, directed and produced several [[Feature film|feature length]] documentary films.<ref>[https://english.crew-united.com/?bio=55111 Birkenstock\u2018s english profile at Crew United]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In 2011 und 2014 he was awarded with the German Film Academy Award LOLA. His documentary feature \"Beltracchi - the Art of Forgery\" had its US theatrical release on August 19, 2015 at [[Film Forum]],  [[New York City]] and [[Laemmle Theatres]], [[Los Angeles]], distributed by Kimstim. As a producer he works with acclaimed directors like David Bernet (Democracy), Viviane Blumenschein (midsummer nights tango), Uli Gaulke (Comrades in Dream), Florian Opitz (The Big Sellout)[[Enrique S\u00e1nchez Lansch]] ([[Rhythm Is It!]]), [[Tonje Hessen Schei]] ([[Drone (2014 film)|Drone]]), [[Milo Rau]] (The Congo Tribunal), Yasemin and Nesrin Samdereli ([[Almanya: Welcome to Germany]]). \n\nBirkenstock is a board member in the [[Deutsche Filmakademie]]. He is also a member of the [[European Film Academy]].,<ref>[http://www.europeanfilmacademy.org/Members.44.0.html#B Birkenstock among the members]</ref> and the German Documentary Association (AG DOK).<ref>[http://www.agdok.de/de_DE/about/vorstand Homepage of the German Documentary Association (AG DOK) ]</ref> Birkenstocks serves as a jury member for film funds in [[Germany]] and [[Switzerland]].\n\n==Filmography==\n* ''[[12 Tangos]] - Adios Buenos Aires'' - Cinema documentary on several dancers who emigrate from Buenos Aires.<ref>[http://www.german-films.de/film-archive/browse-archive/?cHash=73734d235e9d6d69c57da1d0c47ff296&film_id=1419&tx_moviedb_pi2%5Bview%5D=detail&cHash=304d1f70208d4bb534fd226362b345ca&redirect=yes German Films on 12 Tangos]</ref> The film features an All Star Tango Orchestra with some of the most famous argentinian musicians such as Juan Jos\u00e9 \"Pepe\" Libertella, [[Lidia Borda]] and others. 86 min, 2005.<ref>[http://www.tangotales.com/archive/ArneBirkenstock.htm Review and Interview on Tangotales] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120423183111/http://www.tangotales.com/archive/ArneBirkenstock.htm |date=April 23, 2012 }}</ref> It was shown in German theatres and broadcast in ARTE<ref>[http://www.arte.tv/de/12-Tangos/1378126.html 12 Tangos at ARTE TV] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130112181538/http://www.arte.tv/de/12-Tangos/1378126.html |date=January 12, 2013 }}</ref> and other TV channels worldwide.\n* ''[[Chandani - The daughter of the elephant whisperer]]'' - Cinema Documentary about a young girl who wants to become a [[Mahout]] in [[Sri Lanka]] 90 min, 2010<ref>[http://www.german-films.de/film-archive/browse-archive/?cHash=73734d235e9d6d69c57da1d0c47ff296&film_id=1835&mode=filmarchive&tx_moviedb_pi2%5bview%5d=detail&redirect=yes German Films on Chandani]</ref>\n* ''Sound of Heimat'' - Cinema Documentary about Folk music from Germany. 90 min, had its theatrical release in September 2012<ref>[http://theglamourcave.blogspot.co.uk/2012/12/the-sound-of-heimat-or-why-do-germans.html Emma Hartley\u2018s Blog on Birkenstock\u2018s documentary Sound of Heimat]</ref><ref>[http://www.dw.de/insight-germany-talk-show-2013-01-16/e-16482270-9798 45' TV-Interview with [[Hayden Chisholm]] at \"Insight Germany\" (DW TV) about Sound of Heimat] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130122092015/http://www.dw.de/insight-germany-talk-show-2013-01-16/e-16482270-9798 |date=January 22, 2013 }}</ref>\n* ''[[The Art of Forgery]]'' is a [[Documentary film]] about [[Wolfgang Beltracchi]] and the biggest Art Forgery scandal in post war Germany, 90 min., started in German theaters in March 2014 and had its world premier at the Montral World Film Festival.<ref>[https://www.welt.de/print/welt_kompakt/koeln/article106429439/Anwaltssohn-dreht-Film-ueber-Kunstfaelscher-Beltracchi.html Die Welt on Arne Birkenstock shooting a film with Beltracchi]</ref><ref>[http://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2012/10/wolfgang-beltracchi-helene-art-scam Vanity Fair on the Beltracchi case]</ref> The film will be distributed worldwide by Global Screen.<ref>[http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/cannes-2012-match-factory-takes-320374 Hollywood Reporter on Global Screen distributing Arne Birkenstock\u2018s new Documentary]</ref>\n* ''The Moscow Trials''. Cinema Documentary and theatre event by [[Milo Rau]], who assembled the protagonists of the trials about [[Pussy Riot]] and two art exhibits in a staged court house in Moscow in March 2013.<ref>[http://latitude.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/03/04/in-russia-political-theater-becomes-life-in-the-moscow-trials/?_r=0] The New York Times on Milo Raus documentary play and film \"The Moscow Trials\"]</ref>\n*\"The Night of the Nights\" - Cinema Documentary of [[Yasemin \u015eamdereli]] and [[Nesrin \u015eamdereli]] about four couples in Germany, Turkey, Argentina and the USA who have been married for 60 and more years and had a \"real\" wedding night.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arnebirkenstock.de/fruitmarket-2/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-09-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130902230737/http://www.arnebirkenstock.de/fruitmarket-2/ |archivedate=2013-09-02 }} Fruitmarket produces new \u015eamdereli-Film</ref>\n* ''7000 KM from Home'' \u2013 TV documentary series about German foreign exchange students in China, 4 x 30 min., 2008<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newyorkfestivals.com/main.php?p%3D3%2C1%26wp%3Dinfo%26id%3D401085 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-06-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120521223423/https://www.newyorkfestivals.com/main.php?p=3%2C1 |archivedate=2012-05-21 }} 7000KM is a finalist at New York Festival</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\nThe theatrical documentary ''Chandani - The daughter of the elephant whisperer'' was awarded with the [[German Film Award]] as best Children's Feature<ref>[https://www.welt.de/print/welt_kompakt/vermischtes/article13134889/Bester-Kinderfilm-kommt-aus-Koeln.html Die Welt on Arne Birkenstock winning the German Film Award Lola]</ref> and as Best Documentary at the [[Chicago International Children's Film Festival]].<ref>[http://www.cicff.org/bin/file/docs/Award%20List%202010.pdf Chandani at Chicago International Children's Film Festival] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120504131231/http://www.cicff.org/bin/file/docs/Award%20List%202010.pdf |date=May 4, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nThe documentary \"Beltracchi - The Art of Forgery\" was awarded 2014 with the  [[German Film Award]]  \"Lola\" as \"best documentary\".<ref>[http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/german-film-academy-awards-announce-691863 Hollywood Reporter on German film award nominees]</ref>\n\nThe documentary \"The Congo Tribunal\" was awarded 2018 with the Zurich Film Award and nominated for the [[Swiss Film Award]] and for [[German Film Award]] \"Lola\" as \"best documentary\".\n\nThe documentary \"The Night of All Nights\" was awarded 2018 with the [[Bavarian Film Awards]] as \"best Documentary\".\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* http://www.fruitmarket.de/\n* http://www.chandani.realfictionfilme.de\n* {{IMDb name|1920707|Arne Birkenstock}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Birkenstock, Arne}}\n[[Category:German documentary film directors]]\n[[Category:1967 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|German film director and screenwriter|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n'''Arne Birkenstock''' (born 1967) is a German [[film director]] and [[screenwriter]].\n\n==History==\nArne Birkenstock was born in Huettental, [[Germany]] and was raised in [[Cologne]], [[Germany]]. Birkenstock studied [[economy]], [[political Science]], [[History of Latin America]] and [[Romance Languages]] in [[Cologne]], [[Germany]], [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]] and [[C\u00f3rdoba, Argentina|C\u00f3rdoba]], [[Argentina]] and received a [[Master's degree]] in [[Latin American Studies]].{{citation needed|date=October 2012}}\n\nBirkenstock published several studies and non-fiction books on Latin American music and on arts and media policy for German publishing houses and governmental institutions. He has written, directed and produced several [[Feature film|feature length]] documentary films.<ref>[https://english.crew-united.com/?bio=55111 Birkenstock\u2018s english profile at Crew United]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In 2011 und 2014 he was awarded with the German Film Academy Award LOLA. His documentary feature \"Beltracchi - the Art of Forgery\" had its US theatrical release on August 19, 2015 at [[Film Forum]],  [[New York City]] and [[Laemmle Theatres]], [[Los Angeles]], distributed by Kimstim. As a producer he works with acclaimed directors like David Bernet (Democracy), Viviane Blumenschein (midsummer nights tango), Uli Gaulke (Comrades in Dream), Florian Opitz (The Big Sellout)[[Enrique S\u00e1nchez Lansch]] ([[Rhythm Is It!]]), Tonje Hessen Schei ([[Drone (2014 film)|Drone]]), [[Milo Rau]] (The Congo Tribunal), Yasemin and Nesrin Samdereli ([[Almanya: Welcome to Germany]]). \n\nBirkenstock is a board member in the [[Deutsche Filmakademie]]. He is also a member of the [[European Film Academy]].,<ref>[http://www.europeanfilmacademy.org/Members.44.0.html#B Birkenstock among the members]</ref> and the German Documentary Association (AG DOK).<ref>[http://www.agdok.de/de_DE/about/vorstand Homepage of the German Documentary Association (AG DOK) ]</ref> Birkenstocks serves as a jury member for film funds in [[Germany]] and [[Switzerland]].\n\n==Filmography==\n* ''[[12 Tangos]] - Adios Buenos Aires'' - Cinema documentary on several dancers who emigrate from Buenos Aires.<ref>[http://www.german-films.de/film-archive/browse-archive/?cHash=73734d235e9d6d69c57da1d0c47ff296&film_id=1419&tx_moviedb_pi2%5Bview%5D=detail&cHash=304d1f70208d4bb534fd226362b345ca&redirect=yes German Films on 12 Tangos]</ref> The film features an All Star Tango Orchestra with some of the most famous argentinian musicians such as Juan Jos\u00e9 \"Pepe\" Libertella, [[Lidia Borda]] and others. 86 min, 2005.<ref>[http://www.tangotales.com/archive/ArneBirkenstock.htm Review and Interview on Tangotales] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120423183111/http://www.tangotales.com/archive/ArneBirkenstock.htm |date=April 23, 2012 }}</ref> It was shown in German theatres and broadcast in ARTE<ref>[http://www.arte.tv/de/12-Tangos/1378126.html 12 Tangos at ARTE TV] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130112181538/http://www.arte.tv/de/12-Tangos/1378126.html |date=January 12, 2013 }}</ref> and other TV channels worldwide.\n* ''[[Chandani - The daughter of the elephant whisperer]]'' - Cinema Documentary about a young girl who wants to become a [[Mahout]] in [[Sri Lanka]] 90 min, 2010<ref>[http://www.german-films.de/film-archive/browse-archive/?cHash=73734d235e9d6d69c57da1d0c47ff296&film_id=1835&mode=filmarchive&tx_moviedb_pi2%5bview%5d=detail&redirect=yes German Films on Chandani]</ref>\n* ''Sound of Heimat'' - Cinema Documentary about Folk music from Germany. 90 min, had its theatrical release in September 2012<ref>[http://theglamourcave.blogspot.co.uk/2012/12/the-sound-of-heimat-or-why-do-germans.html Emma Hartley\u2018s Blog on Birkenstock\u2018s documentary Sound of Heimat]</ref><ref>[http://www.dw.de/insight-germany-talk-show-2013-01-16/e-16482270-9798 45' TV-Interview with [[Hayden Chisholm]] at \"Insight Germany\" (DW TV) about Sound of Heimat] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130122092015/http://www.dw.de/insight-germany-talk-show-2013-01-16/e-16482270-9798 |date=January 22, 2013 }}</ref>\n* ''[[The Art of Forgery]]'' is a [[Documentary film]] about [[Wolfgang Beltracchi]] and the biggest Art Forgery scandal in post war Germany, 90 min., started in German theaters in March 2014 and had its world premier at the Montral World Film Festival.<ref>[https://www.welt.de/print/welt_kompakt/koeln/article106429439/Anwaltssohn-dreht-Film-ueber-Kunstfaelscher-Beltracchi.html Die Welt on Arne Birkenstock shooting a film with Beltracchi]</ref><ref>[http://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2012/10/wolfgang-beltracchi-helene-art-scam Vanity Fair on the Beltracchi case]</ref> The film will be distributed worldwide by Global Screen.<ref>[http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/cannes-2012-match-factory-takes-320374 Hollywood Reporter on Global Screen distributing Arne Birkenstock\u2018s new Documentary]</ref>\n* ''The Moscow Trials''. Cinema Documentary and theatre event by [[Milo Rau]], who assembled the protagonists of the trials about [[Pussy Riot]] and two art exhibits in a staged court house in Moscow in March 2013.<ref>[http://latitude.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/03/04/in-russia-political-theater-becomes-life-in-the-moscow-trials/?_r=0] The New York Times on Milo Raus documentary play and film \"The Moscow Trials\"]</ref>\n*\"The Night of the Nights\" - Cinema Documentary of [[Yasemin \u015eamdereli]] and [[Nesrin \u015eamdereli]] about four couples in Germany, Turkey, Argentina and the USA who have been married for 60 and more years and had a \"real\" wedding night.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arnebirkenstock.de/fruitmarket-2/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-09-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130902230737/http://www.arnebirkenstock.de/fruitmarket-2/ |archivedate=2013-09-02 }} Fruitmarket produces new \u015eamdereli-Film</ref>\n* ''7000 KM from Home'' \u2013 TV documentary series about German foreign exchange students in China, 4 x 30 min., 2008<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newyorkfestivals.com/main.php?p%3D3%2C1%26wp%3Dinfo%26id%3D401085 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-06-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120521223423/https://www.newyorkfestivals.com/main.php?p=3%2C1 |archivedate=2012-05-21 }} 7000KM is a finalist at New York Festival</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\nThe theatrical documentary ''Chandani - The daughter of the elephant whisperer'' was awarded with the [[German Film Award]] as best Children's Feature<ref>[https://www.welt.de/print/welt_kompakt/vermischtes/article13134889/Bester-Kinderfilm-kommt-aus-Koeln.html Die Welt on Arne Birkenstock winning the German Film Award Lola]</ref> and as Best Documentary at the [[Chicago International Children's Film Festival]].<ref>[http://www.cicff.org/bin/file/docs/Award%20List%202010.pdf Chandani at Chicago International Children's Film Festival] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120504131231/http://www.cicff.org/bin/file/docs/Award%20List%202010.pdf |date=May 4, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nThe documentary \"Beltracchi - The Art of Forgery\" was awarded 2014 with the  [[German Film Award]]  \"Lola\" as \"best documentary\".<ref>[http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/german-film-academy-awards-announce-691863 Hollywood Reporter on German film award nominees]</ref>\n\nThe documentary \"The Congo Tribunal\" was awarded 2018 with the Zurich Film Award and nominated for the [[Swiss Film Award]] and for [[German Film Award]] \"Lola\" as \"best documentary\".\n\nThe documentary \"The Night of All Nights\" was awarded 2018 with the [[Bavarian Film Awards]] as \"best Documentary\".\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* http://www.fruitmarket.de/\n* http://www.chandani.realfictionfilme.de\n* {{IMDb name|1920707|Arne Birkenstock}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Birkenstock, Arne}}\n[[Category:German documentary film directors]]\n[[Category:1967 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "Geysirhead", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eHistory:added link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arne_Birkenstock"}
