age Christian School (Canton, Ohio)|Heritage Christian School]]''' Conquerors (no football)\n* Cleveland '''Northeast Ohio College Preparatory''' Knights (no football)\n* Lakewood '''[[St. Edward High School (Lakewood, Ohio)|St. Edward]]''' Eagles\n* Cleveland '''[[Saint Ignatius High School (Cleveland)|St. Ignatius]]''' Wildcats\n* Ashtabula '''[[Saint John School (Ashtabula, Ohio)|St. John]]''' Fighting Heralds\n* Akron '''[[St. Vincent \u2013 St. Mary High School|St. Vincent-St. Mary]]''' Fighting Irish\n* Hunting Valley '''[[University School|University]]''' Preppers\n* Youngstown '''[[Ursuline High School (Youngstown, Ohio)|Ursuline]]''' Fighting Irish\n* Massillon '''[[Massillon Washington High School|Washington]]''' Tigers\n* '''[[Louisville High School (Ohio)|Louisville]]''' Leopards\n\n==Lake Effect Conference==\n*Willoughby '''[[Andrews Osborne Academy]]''' Phoenix (2012-)\n*Elyria  '''[[First Baptist Christian School (Elyria, Ohio)|First Baptist Christian]]''' Sabres (2012-)\n*Austinburg '''[[Grand River Academy|Grand River]]''' Eagles (2012-)\n*Chagrin Falls '''Geauga''' Grizzlies (2012-)\n*North Olmsted  '''HEARTS for Jesus Christ''' Guardians (2012-)\n*Cleveland '''[[Horizon Science Academy- Cleveland High School|Horizon Science]]''' Dragons (2012-)\n*North Ridgeville '''[[Lake Ridge Academy]]''' Royals (2016-)\n*Sagamore Hills '''[[Lawrence School (Sagamore Hills, Ohio)|Lawrence]]''' Lions (2012-)\n*Cleveland '''[[St. Martin de Porres High School (Cleveland, Ohio)|St. Martin De Porres]]''' Lions (2012-)\n\nThis conference does not include football. Only Cleveland St. Martin De Porres, Cleveland Horizon Science Academy,  North Ridgeville Lake Ridge Academy, and Willoughby Andrews Osborne Academy are current members of the OHSAA.\n\n==Lake Erie League==\n*'''[[Bedford High School (Ohio)|Bedford]]''' Bearcats (1998-)\n*'''[[Cleveland Heights High School|Cleveland Heights]]''' Tigers (1928-)\n*'''[[Lorain City School District#High schools|Lorain]]''' Titans (2010-)\n*'''[[Maple Heights High School|Maple Heights]]''' Mustangs (1998-)\n* '''[[Shaker Heights High School|Shaker Heights]]''' Red Raiders (1923-2012, to Northeast Ohio, 2020-)\n*East Cleveland '''[[Shaw High School (Ohio)|Shaw]]''' Cardinals (1928-)\n*'''[[Warrensville Heights High School|Warrensville Heights]]''' Tigers (1993-, [Football 1993\u20132014, 2016-]) \n*Cleveland Heights '''[[Lutheran High School East|Lutheran East]]''' Falcons (2017-) (all sports except football)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.morningjournal.com/sports/20160730/high-school-sports-lake-erie-league-to-add-lutheran-east|title=High school sports: Lake Erie League to add Lutheran East|access-date=2016-08-04}}</ref>\n\n'''Former members'''\n* '''[[Elyria High School|Elyria]]''' Pioneers (1923\u201354, to Buckeye Conference. 1997\u20132003, to Pioneer)\n* '''[[Lakewood High School (Lakewood, Ohio)|Lakewood]]''' Rangers (1923-2007, to Northeast Ohio)\n* '''Lorain''' Steelmen (1923\u201354, to Buckeye Conference)\n* '''[[Rocky River High School (Ohio)|Rocky River]]''' Pirates (1923\u201337, to Southwestern)\n* '''[[Parma Senior High School|Parma]]''' Redmen (1951-2003, to Pioneer)\n* Lyndhurst '''[[Charles F. Brush High School|Brush]]''' Arcs (1962\u201375, to Greater Cleveland)\n* Parma Heights '''[[Valley Forge High School|Valley Forge]]''' Patriots (1962-2003, to Pioneer)\n* '''[[Garfield Heights High School|Garfield Heights]]''' Bulldogs (1968-2007, to Northeast Ohio [Football 1968\u201386, 1993-2007])\n* Parma '''[[Normandy High School (Ohio)|Normandy]]''' Invaders (1968-2003, to Pioneer)\n* '''[[Berea High School|Berea]]''' Braves (1975\u201379, to Pioneer)\n* Middleburg Heights '''[[Midpark High School|Midpark]]''' Meteors (1975\u201379, to Pioneer)\n* '''[[Mentor High School|Mentor]]''' Cardinals (1993-2011, to Northeast Ohio)\n* '''[[Euclid High School|Euclid]]''' Panthers (1998-2015, to Greater Cleveland)\n* Lorain '''Admiral King''' Admirals (2002\u201310, consolidated into Lorain)\n* Lorain '''Southview''' Saints (2002\u201310, consolidated into Lorain)\n* Warren '''[[Warren G. Harding High School|Warren G. Harding]]''' Raiders (2010-2013, to All-American, football through 2014 season)\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+align=bottom style=\"text-align:left;\"|\n|- style=\"background:#ccf;\"\n! colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#ddd;\"| Lake Erie League Divisions (1993-2011, unless noted)\n|-\n! {{color box|#3C3B6E|Lake Division|white}}\n! {{color box|#B22234|Erie Division|white}}\n|-\n| Admiral King (2002\u201306)\n| Admiral King (2006\u201310)\n|-\n| Cleveland Heights\n| Bedford (1998-2011)\n|-\n| Elyria (1997-2003)\n| Garfield Heights (1993-2007)\n|-\n| Euclid (1998-2011)\n| Lorain (2010\u201311)\n|-\n| Lakewood (1993-2007)\n| Maple Heights (1998-2006, 2010\u201311)\n|-\n| Maple Heights (2006\u201310)\n| Normandy (1993-2003)\n|-\n| Mentor\n| Parma (1993-2003)\n|-\n| Shaker Heights (1997-2011)\n| Shaker Heights (1993\u201397)\n|- \n| Shaw (1993\u201397)\n| Shaw (1997-2011)\n|-\n| Southview (2002\u201303)\n| Southview (2003\u201310)\n|-\n| Valley Forge (1993-2002)\n| Valley Forge (2002\u201303)\n|-\n| Warren Harding (2010\u201311)\n| Warrensville Heights\n|}\n\n==Lorain County League/Conference==\nOriginally began in 1924 as one of the small-school county leagues, the league survived the consolidation wave until 1961, when the schools who weren't already aligned with the Inland Conference joined the Lakeland Conference. The conference revived itself in 1986, as the Lakeland collapsed, and the schools banded together for roughly two decades until the schools split, this time to help form the Patriot Athletic and West Shore conferences. The third and current version of the league formed in 2019 from the remnants of the Patriot Athletic Conference.\n\n'''Third Version (Lorain County League, 2019-)\n* Sullivan '''[[Black River High School (Sullivan, Ohio)|Black River]]''' Pirates (2019-)\n* Sheffield '''[[Brookside High School|Brookside]]''' Cardinals (2019-)\n* Lorain '''[[Clearview High School (Lorain, Ohio)|Clearview]]''' Clippers (2019-)\n* Columbia Station '''[[Columbia High School (Columbia Station, Ohio)|Columbia]]''' Raiders (2019-)\n* Oberlin '''[[Firelands High School (Oberlin, Ohio)|Firelands]]''' Falcons (2019-)\n* LaGrange '''[[Keystone High School (LaGrange, Ohio)|Keystone]]''' Wildcats (2019-)\n* '''[[Oberlin High School (Ohio)|Oberlin]]''' Indians (2019-)\n* '''[[Wellington High School (Wellington, Ohio)|Wellington]]''' Dukes (2019-)\n\n'''Second Version (Lorain County Conference, 1986-2005)\n* '''[[Avon High School (Avon, Ohio)|Avon]]''' Eagles (1986\u20132005, to West Shore)\n* Sheffield '''[[Brookside High School|Brookside]]''' Cardinals (1986\u20132005, to Patriot)\n* Lorain '''[[Clearview High School (Lorain, Ohio)|Clearview]]''' Clippers (1986\u20132005, to Patriot)\n* Oberlin '''[[Firelands High School (Oberlin, Ohio)|Firelands]]''' Falcons (1986\u20132005, to West Shore)\n* LaGrange '''[[Keystone High School (LaGrange, Ohio)|Keystone]]''' Wildcats (1986\u20132005, to Patriot)\n* '''[[Oberlin High School (Ohio)|Oberlin]]''' Indians (1986\u20132005, to Patriot)\n* '''[[Wellington High School (Wellington, Ohio)|Wellington]]''' Dukes (1986\u20132005, to Patriot)\n* Elyria '''West''' Wolverines (1986\u20131996, school closed, consolidated into Elyria)\n* Grafton '''[[Midview High School (Grafton, Ohio)|Midview]]''' Middies (1996\u20132005, to West SHore)\n\n'''First Version (Lorain County League, 1924\u201361)'''\n* '''[[Avon High School (Avon, Ohio)|Avon]]''' Eagles<sup>1</sup> (1924\u201361, to Inland)\n* '''[[Avon Lake High School|Avon Lake]]''' Shoremen (1924\u20131961, to Lakeland)\n* '''Belden''' Bees (1924\u201355, consolidated into Midview)\n* '''Brighton''' Bears (1924\u201352, consolidated into Wellington)\n* Sheffield '''[[Brookside High School|Brookside]]''' Cardinals<sup>1</sup> (1924\u201361, to Inland)\n* '''Brownhelm''' Bombers (1924\u201352, consolidated into Firelands)\n* Kipton '''Camden''' Knights (1924\u201352, consolidated into Firelands)\n* Columbia Station '''[[Columbia High School (Columbia Station, Ohio)|Columbia]]''' Raiders<sup>1</sup> (1924\u201361, to Inland)\n* Grafton '''Eaton''' Eels (1924\u201355, consolidated into Midview)\n* '''Grafton''' Comets (1924\u201355, consolidated into Midview)\n* '''Henrietta''' Hawks (1924\u201352, consolidated into Firelands)\n* '''LaGrange''' Wildcats (1924\u201359, consolidated into Keystone)\n* '''[[North Ridgeville]]''' Rangers (1924\u201327, to NOAL, 1933\u201361, to Lakeland)\n* '''Penfield''' Bombers (1924\u201359, consolidated into Keystone)\n* '''[[South Amherst High School|South Amherst]]''' Cavaliers<sup>1</sup> (1924\u201361, to Inland)\n* '''[[Wellington High School (Wellington, Ohio)|Wellington]]''' Dukes (1924\u201327, to NOAL)\n* Lorain '''[[Clearview High School (Lorain, Ohio)|Clearview]]''' Clippers (1928\u201338, to NOAL, 1947\u201353, to Lakeland)\n* Oberlin '''[[Firelands High School (Oberlin, Ohio)|Firelands]]''' Falcons<sup>1</sup> (1952\u201361, to Inland)\n* Grafton '''[[Midview High School (Grafton, Ohio)|Midview]]''' Middies (1955\u201361, to Lakeland)\n* Lagrange '''[[Keystone High School (LaGrange, Ohio)|Keystone]]''' Wildcats<sup>2</sup> (1959\u201361)\n\n# Concurrent with Inland Conference 1957\u201361.\n# Concurrent with Inland Conference 1959\u201361.\n\n'''Division Alignments'''\n\n{{Col-begin}}\n{{Col-break}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#ddd;\"| LCL Divisions 1924-38\n|-\n! Eastern\n! Western\n|-\n| Avon\n| Brighton\n|-\n| Avon Lake\n| Brownhelm\n|-\n| Belden\n| Camden\n|-\n| Brookside\n| Clearfield (1928\u201338)\n|-\n| Columbia\n| Henrietta\n|-\n| Eaton\n| LaGrange (1933\u201338)\n|-\n| Grafton\n| Oberlin (1924\u201337)\n|-\n| LaGrange (1928\u201333)\n| Penfield\n|-\n| North Ridgeville (1924\u201327, 1933-)\n| South Amherst\n|-\n| \n| Wellington (1924\u201327)\n|}\n\n{{Col-break}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan