orresponding high schools do not always match and because there is often a possibility of ambiguity with respect to either the name of a locality or the name of a high school, the following table gives both in every case, with the locality name first, in plain type, and the high school name second in '''boldface''' type. The school's team nickname is given last.\n\n==Akron City Series==\n{{Main|Akron City Series}}\n* Akron '''[[Buchtel High School|Buchtel]]''' Griffins (1931-)\n* Akron '''[[East Community Learning Center|East]]''' Dragons (1918-)\n* Akron '''[[Ellet High School|Ellet]]''' Orangemen (1971-)\n* Akron '''[[Firestone High School|Firestone]]''' Falcons (1963-)\n* Akron '''[[Kenmore-Garfield High School|Kenmore-Garfield]]''' Golden Rams (2017-)\n* Akron '''[[North High School (Akron, Ohio)|North]]''' Vikings (1915-)\n\n'''Former members'''\n* Akron '''Central''' Wildcats (1915-1970, consolidated into Central-Hower)\n* Akron '''[[Central-Hower High School|Central-Hower]]''' Eagles (1970-2006, closed)\n* Akron '''[[Garfield High School (Akron, Ohio)|Garfield]]''' Rams (1926-2017, consolidated into Kenmore-Garfield)\n* Akron '''Hower''' Buccaneers (1927-1970, consolidated into Central-Hower)\n* Akron '''[[Kenmore High School|Kenmore]]''' Cardinals (1929-2017, consolidated into Kenmore-Garfield)\n* Akron '''[[South High School (Akron, Ohio)|South]]''' Cavaliers or Big Blue (1915-1980, closed)\n* Akron '''[[West High School (Akron, Ohio)|West]]''' Cowboys (1915-1953, closed)\n\n==All-American Conference==\n{{Main|All-American Conference}}\n\n'''Gold Division'''\n* '''[[Austintown-Fitch High School|Austintown-Fitch]]''' Falcons (2011- [Football, 2015-])\n* Youngstown '''[[Boardman High School|Boardman]]''' Spartans (2014- [Football, 2015-])\n* '''[[Warren G. Harding High School|Warren G. Harding]]''' Raiders (2014- [Football, 2015-])\n\n'''Red Division'''\n* '''[[Canfield High School (Ohio)|Canfield]]''' Cardinals (2008-)\n* Warren '''[[Howland High School|Howland]]''' Tigers (2008-)\n\n'''Blue Division'''\n* '''[[Brookfield High School (Brookfield, Ohio)|Brookfield]]''' Warriors (2014-)\n* Campbell '''[[Campbell Memorial High School (Ohio)|Memorial]]''' Red Devils (2008-)\n* Warren '''[[Champion High School|Champion]]''' Golden Flashes (2008-)\n* Columbiana '''[[Crestview High School (Columbiana, Ohio)|Crestview]]''' Rebels (2019-)\n* Leavittsburg '''[[LaBrae High School|LaBrae]]''' Vikings (2008-)\n* Youngstown '''[[Liberty High School (Ohio)|Liberty]]''' Leopards (2008-)\n* '''[[Newton Falls, Ohio|Newton Falls]]''' Tigers (2008-)\n'''Former members'''\n* Lisbon '''[[Beaver Local High School|Beaver Local]]''' Beavers (played concurrently in [[Ohio Valley Athletic Conference|OVAC]], 2008\u201313) Red Division 2008\u201311, American Division 2011\u201313.\n* '''[[Girard High School (Ohio)|Girard]]''' Indians (2008-2018 (football after 2018 season), to Northeast 8)\n* '''[[Hubbard High School (Ohio)|Hubbard]]''' Eagles (2008-2018 (football after 2018 season), to Northeast 8)\n* '''[[Jefferson Area High School (Jefferson, Ohio)|Jefferson Area]]''' Falcons (2011-2018 (football after 2018 season), to Northeast 8)\n* Cortland '''[[Lakeview High School (Ohio)|Lakeview]]''' Bulldogs (2008-2018 (football after 2018 season), to Northeast 8)\n* '''[[Niles McKinley High School|Niles McKinley]]''' Red Dragons (2008-2018 (football after 2018 season), to Northeast 8)\n* Poland '''[[Poland Seminary High School|Poland Seminary]]''' Bulldogs (2008-2018 (football after 2018 season), to Northeast 8)\n* '''[[Salem High School (Ohio)|Salem]]''' Quakers (2008\u201311, left for [[Northeastern Buckeye Conference]]) White Division 2008\u201311.\n* '''[[Struthers High School|Struthers]]''' Wildcats (2008-2018 (football after 2018 season), to Northeast 8)\n* Ashtabula '''[[Edgewood Senior High School|Edgewood]]''' Warriors (2014-2019)\n* '''[[Lakeside High School (Ashtabula, Ohio)|Ashtabula Lakeside]]''' Dragons (2015-2019)\n* Youngstown '''[[East 