h Asia &#124; At least nineteen dead in Indian bus accident |work=BBC News |date=14 December 1998 |accessdate=7 February 2013}}</ref>\n*23 December \u2014 At least 21 people killed when a bus collided with a large truck.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/241169.stm |title=Africa &#124; South Africa bus crash kills 21 |work=BBC News |date=23 December 1998 |accessdate=7 February 2013}}</ref>\n*25 December \u2014 At least 19 people killed in [[Andhra Pradesh]] when a bus crashed into a train.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/south_asia/180028.stm |title=South Asia &#124; School children die in mishap |work=BBC News |date=25 September 1998 |accessdate=7 February 2013}}</ref>\n* 31 December \u2014 100 cars crashed on an ice-slicked section of Interstate-75 in central [[Michigan]], killing one and injuring 39.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20010719211057/http://www.cnn.com/US/9812/31/michigan.pileup/ Car-pileup in snowy Michigan kills 1] CNN. 31 December 1998. Archived 19 July 2001.</ref>\n\n===1999===\n* 4 January \u2014 A local bus carrying 40 passengers exploded and blast ripped at outskirt of [[Linghai]], [[Jinzhou]], [[Liaoning]], China, killing 18 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 9 January \u2014 A bus carrying funeral mourners ran off the road and plunged into a river below of 750 feet at outskirt of [[Kazbegi]], [[Khevi]], Georgia, killing 38 people.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/251424.stm |title=Europe &#124; 38 found dead in Georgia bus accident |work=BBC News |date=9 January 1999 |accessdate=7 February 2013}}</ref>\n*21 January \u2014 At least 22 were killed when a bus fell into a ravine near the town of Baguio on Wednesday night.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/259708.stm |title=Asia-Pacific &#124; Philippines bus crash kills 22 |work=BBC News |date=21 January 1999 |accessdate=7 February 2013}}</ref>\n* 24 January \u2014 A bus carrying Hungarian skiers plunged off a hillside on the outskirts of [[Deutschlandsberg]], [[Styria]], Austria, killing 18 people and injuring 32.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/262158.stm | work=BBC News | title=Bus crash kills 18 in Austria | date=25 January 1999 | accessdate=8 May 2010}}</ref>\n{{main|1999 Deutschlandsberg bus crash}}\n*31 January \u2014 At least 31 killed when a bus plunged off a bridge.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/269409.stm |title=Africa &#124; Thirty one killed in South African bus accident |work=BBC News |date=31 January 1999 |accessdate=7 February 2013}}</ref>\n*26 February  \u2014 A minibus east of [[Karlskoga]], Sweden got stuck on a truck, was dragged along and finally caught fire. Seven children and two teachers, were killed.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://wwwc.aftonbladet.se/nyheter/9902/26/tank2.html |newspaper=[[Aftonbladet]] |title=Nio dog i olyckan i morse |trans-title=Nine died in the accident this morning |first1=Britt |last1=Peruzzi |first2=Filip |last2=Hammar |author-link2=Filip Hammar |date=26 February 1999 |access-date=22 March 2016 |language=Swedish}}</ref>\n* 15 March \u2014 The train ''[[City of New Orleans (train)|City of New Orleans]]'' collides with a truck and derails in [[Bourbonnais, Illinois]], United States, killing 11 people.\n{{main|1999 Bourbonnais, Illinois, train crash}}\n* 24 March \u2014 39 people killed in the [[Mont Blanc Tunnel]] fire.\n* 30 April \u2014 A small vehicle collides with a stopped tanker truck loaded with propane and starts a fire near [[Kamena Vourla|Kamena Vourla, Fthiotis]]. A huge explosion follows several minutes later killing 5 people and injuring 14.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.tovima.gr/society/article/?aid=236591 | work=\u03a4\u039f \u0392\u0397\u039c\u0391 | title=\u039a\u03b9\u03bd\u03bf\u03cd\u03bc\u03b5\u03bd\u03b5\u03c2 \u03b2\u03cc\u03bc\u03b2\u03b5\u03c2 \u03bc\u03ad\u03c3\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf\u03cd\u03bd\u03b5\u03bb | date=14 May 2008 | accessdate=15 March 2012}}</ref>\n* 9 May \u2014 A bus slipped and plunged down a 680-foot slope at [[Kapurbot Bazar]], Saiyan, [[Rapti Zone|Rapti]], Nepal, killing 32 people and injuring 36. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 9 May \u2014 A tour bus crashes into a concrete wall on [[Interstate 610 (Louisiana)|Interstate 610]] in [[New Orleans]], killing 22 people and injuring 24.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/US/9905/10/louisiana.bus.crash.02/index.html?eref=sitesearch|title=CNN - Cause of bus crash that killed 22 still a mystery - May 10, 1999|website=www.cnn.com|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref>\n* 21 May \u2014 A truck and a bus are involved in a crash in the town of [[Villa Mercedes|San Luis Province]]. killing 21 people. There were four survivors. ThIs the worst disaster in the history of the province.\n* 29 May \u2014 12 people killed and 50 injured in a collision and fire in [[Tauern Road Tunnel|Tauern Tunnel]] in Austria.\n*6 June \u2013 At least 8 people died on Saturday after a bus burst a tyre and overturned at Naivasha on the main Nairobi to Nakuru highway, in another crash 12 were killed when the bus collided with another vehicle.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/362371.stm |title=Africa &#124; Twenty dead in Kenya crashes |work=BBC News |date=6 June 1999 |accessdate=7 February 2013}}</ref>\n* 8 June \u2014 At least 94 killed including 11 children after a bus plunged into a lake in [[Karnataka]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/south_asia/364901.stm |title=South Asia &#124; Karnataka bus toll rises |work=BBC News |date=9 June 1999 |accessdate=7 February 2013}}</ref>\n* 18 July \u2014 A [[Kiari]]-[[Shimla]] HRTC regular route bus carrying 90 passengers plunged into a 40-foot deep gorge on the outskirts of Baghar, [[Himachal Pradesh]], India, killing 18 people. Another 55 are injured.<ref>''Bus Falls Into Mountain Gorge in Northern India; 14 Killed'' Lethbridge Herald (Alberta); 23 July 1999; p. 11 (available at newspaperarchive.com)</ref>\n* 24 July \u2014 A trailer truck crashes into cars slowed by [[Roadworks|roadwork]] on [[Quebec Autoroute 20]] near [[Saint-Michel-de-Bellechasse]], killing 4 people and injuring 11.<ref>[http://www.radio-canada.ca/regions/quebec/nouvelles/2002/archives/index.asp?val=8075 Carambolage de juillet 1999 \u00e0 Saint-Michel] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110605080424/http://www.radio-canada.ca/regions/quebec/nouvelles/2002/archives/index.asp?val=8075 |date=5 June 2011 }}, 11 September 2000.</ref> A public investigation is launched.\n* 11 August \u2014 An attack on a passenger bus in the town of Fighiera in the [[Santa Fe Province]] causes a strong fire, killing 13 people and injuring five.\n* 3 September \u2014 Dense fog on [[Highway 401 (Ontario)|Highway 401]] near [[Windsor, Ontario]] reduces visibility to less than a meter (3&nbsp;ft) and causes an [[1999 Highway 401 crash|87-vehicle pileup]] and fire that kills 8 people and injures 33. Many vehicles are fused together by the intense heat.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.msc-smc.ec.gc.ca/media/top10/1999_e.html|title=Top Ten Weather Stories of 1999|accessdate=1 October 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060506080834/http://www.msc-smc.ec.gc.ca/media/top10/1999_e.html|archivedate=6 May 2006}}</ref>\n* 14 September \u2014 A long distance regular route bus overturned and plunged into a canyon in the outskirts of [[Kaijiang County|Kaijiang]], [[Dazhou]], [[Sichuan]], China, killing 46 people. Another 9 are injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n*16 September \u2014 Two road crashes in Peru involving buses have killed at least 16 people and injured 48 others.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/448723.stm |title=Americas &#124; Fatal bus crash in Peru |work=BBC News |date=16 September 1999 |accessdate=7 February 2013}}</ref>\n*19 September \u2014 At least 20 people have died in a bus crash.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/451708.stm |title=Europe &#124; 20 die in Spanish bus crash |work=BBC News |date=19 September 1999 |accessdate=1 April 2013}}</ref>\n*22 September \u2014 At least 11 people have been killed in South Africa in a head-on collision between a bus and a truck.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/454323.stm |title=Africa &#124; Eleven killed in South African crash |work=BBC News |date=22 September 1999 |accessdate=1 April 2013}}</ref>\n* 25 September \u2014 A bus went off a highway in foggy weather and crashed in the outskirts of [[Kokstad, KwaZulu-Natal|Kokstad]], [[KwaZulu-Natal]], South Africa, killing 15 people. Another 20 are injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n*4 October \u2014 At least 19 people have been killed and 47 seriously injured after a bus crashed down a river embankment.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/464449.stm |title=Africa &#124; South Africa bus crash kills 19 |work=BBC News |date=4 October 1999 |accessdate=1 April 2013}}</ref>\n* 5 October \u2014 At least 45 people have been killed in a bus crash in the Indonesian province of West Java.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/465655.stm |title=Asia-Pacific &#124; 45 die in Indonesian bus crash |work=BBC News |date=5 October 1999 |accessdate=1 April 2013}}</ref>\n* 9 October \u2014 A tourbus in [[Galilee]], Israel, hit a slick spot on the road, rolled downhill; 17 killed.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.jpost.com/Israel/Tour-company-cleared-for-fatal-Galilee-accident |title=Tour company cleared for fatal Galilee accident |newspaper=Jerusalem Post |date=6 December 2006 |accessdate=22 December 2013}}</ref>\n* 25 October \u2014 A bus swerved to avoid hitting a cow and skidded off a mountain road into a deep gorge, killing 27 and injuring 47 on the way home from a temple in Northern India in [[Hoshiarpur district]], 70 miles northeast of [[Amritsar]].<ref>''India Bus Accident Kills 27 Pilgrims'' Estherville Daily News (Iowa); 26 October 1999 (available at newspaperarchive.com)</ref>\n*7 November \u2014 At least 50 people have died in a bus crash in Indian-administered [[Jammu and Kashmir]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/south_asia/508263.stm |title=South Asia &#124; Over 50 dead in bus crash |work=BBC News |date=7 November 1999 |accessdate=1 April 2013}}</ref>\n* 30 December \u2014 A [[Karachi]]-[[Rawalpindi]] regular route bus overturned and caught fire at [[Lahore]]-[[Islamabad]] M2 expressway, outskirt of [[Kallar Kahar]], [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]] of Pakistan, in an incident caused by excessive speed, killing 48 people. Another 20 are injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of bridge failures]]\n*[[List of level crossing accidents]]\n*[[Lists of rail accidents]] includes [[level crossing]] crashes\n*[[Multiple-vehicle collision]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://moes-garage.spaces.live.com/photos/cns!4FC3316B3CBDCA99!334/ Early Auto Accidents]{{Dead link|date=August 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Photos of Auto Accidents from the 1920s to 1950s\n* [http://www.mapreport.com/subtopics/d/c.html Partial list of Highway disasters]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110717090300/http://www.descansos.org/ Descansos.org :: Project to create awareness of victims of vehicular fatalities.]\n* [http://www.vehiclerecovery.org/history/index.htm A Condensed History of Vehicle Recovery in the United Kingdom.]\n\n{{Road accidents}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List of traffic collisions}}\n[[Category:Lists of traffic collisions| ]]\n[[Category:Traffic collisions|*]]\n[[Category:20th-century road incidents|*]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Dynamic list}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{more citations needed|date=July 2008}}\n{{very long|rps=0.4|date=September 2009}}\n}}\nThis '''list of traffic collisions''' records serious [[traffic collision|road crash]]es: those that have a large [[death toll]], occurred in unusual circumstances, or have some other historical significance. For crashes that killed famous people, refer to [[List of people who died in road accidents]]. The prevalence of bus crashes in this list is a function of severity rather than of frequency.\n\n* [[List of notable traffic collisions (2000\u2013present)]]\n\n__NOTOC__\n<!--begin compact toc-->\n{|\n|-\n!  style=\"background:#ddd; text-align:center;\" colspan=\"11\"| Notable historic road crashes\n|-\n!  style=\"background:#ddd; text-align:right;\"| [[#1950s|1950s]]:\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1950|1950]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1951|1951]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1952|1952]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1953|1953]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1954|1954]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1955|1955]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1956|1956]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1957|1957]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1958|1958]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1959|1959]]\n|-\n!  style=\"background:#ddd; text-align:right;\"| [[#1960s|1960s]]:\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1960|1960]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1961|1961]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1962|1962]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1963|1963]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1964|1964]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1965|1965]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1966|1966]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1967|1967]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1968|1968]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1969|1969]]\n|-\n!  style=\"background:#ddd; text-align:right;\"| [[#1970s|1970s]]:\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1970|1970]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1971|1971]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1972|1972]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1973|1973]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1974|1974]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1975|1975]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1976|1976]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1977|1977]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1978|1978]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1979|1979]]\n|-\n!  style=\"background:#ddd; text-align:right;\"| [[#1980s|1980s]]:\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1980|1980]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1981|1981]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1982|1982]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1983|1983]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1984|1984]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1985|1985]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1986|1986]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1987|1987]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1988|1988]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1989|1989]]\n|-\n!  style=\"background:#ddd; text-align:right;\"| [[#1990s|1990s]]:\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1990|1990]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1991|1991]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1992|1992]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1993|1993]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1994|1994]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1995|1995]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1996|1996]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1997|1997]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1998|1998]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd;\"| [[#1999|1999]]\n|-\n|  style=\"background:#ddd; text-align:center;\" colspan=\"11\"| [[#See also|See also]] \u2014 [[#References|References]] \u2014 [[#External links|External links]]\n|}\n<!--end compact toc-->\n\n<!--\nBecause of the large numbers of potential candidates, only collisions independently notable for some reason should be included (e.g., high death toll, terrorism, worst in a country's history, unusual circumstances).\n-->\n\n==1700s==\n[[File:\"A Typical Cable 'Accident' on Broadway.\", ca. 08-29-1895 - NARA - 513353.tif|thumb|right|220px|\"A Typical Cable 'Accident' on Broadway.\", ca. 29 August 1895]]\n\n* 1771 France \u2013 [[Nicolas-Joseph Cugnot]]'s second [[steam engine|steam-powered]] vehicle is said to have crashed into a wall during a test run, in what would have been the first [[automobile accident]]. However, it is disputed that this ever happened. According to Georges Ageon<ref>{{cite web|title=Le fardier de Cugnot|url=http://www.ile-de-france.drire.gouv.fr/vehicules/homolo/cnrv/histoire.htm|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080416231439/http://www.ile-de-france.drire.gouv.fr/vehicules/homolo/cnrv/histoire.htm|archivedate=16 April 2008}}</ref> the earliest mention of this occurrence dates from 1801 and it does not feature in contemporary accounts.\n\n==1800s==\n* 31 August 1869 Ireland\u2013 While riding as a passenger with relatives in an experimental [[steam car]], [[Mary Ward (scientist)|Mary Ward]] was thrown from the car and fell under the wheels as it rounded a bend. This is believed to be the first recorded automobile death. It took place in the town of [[Birr, County Offaly|Birr]], which was known at that time as Parsonstown. The car was built by her cousins, the sons of [[William Parsons, 3rd Earl of Rosse]].<ref name=\"OHAS\">{{cite web\n | url = http://www.offalyhistory.com/content/reading_resources/famous_people/ward_mary.htm\n | title = Mary Ward 1827\u20131869\n | work = Famous Offaly People\n | publisher = Offaly Historical & Archaeological Society\n | accessdate = 25 April 2006\n|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20060105215309/http://www.offalyhistory.com/content/reading_resources/famous_people/ward_mary.htm |archivedate = 5 January 2006}}</ref>\n* 1890 [[London]] had 5,728 street accidents, resulting in 144 deaths.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/WT18911128.2.11|title=Waikato Times, 1891-11-28|last=|first=|date=|website=paperspast.natlib.govt.nz National Library of New Zealand|language=en|access-date=21 April 2017}}</ref> It may be that not all of these involved motorized carriages.\n* 1891 US. [[John William Lambert]], was involved in the first recorded automobile accident in American history. The accident occurred in Ohio City, Ohio. Lambert's vehicle\u2014the first single-cylinder gasoline automobile, which was carrying Lambert and James Swoveland, hit a tree root, causing the car to careen out of control and smash into a hitching post. Injuries from this accident were minor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ohiohistorycentral.org/entry.php?rec=2596 |title=World's First Automobile Accident \u2013 Ohio History Central \u2013 A product of the Ohio Historical Society |publisher=Ohio History Central |date=27 July 2006 |accessdate=1 April 2013}}</ref>\n* 17 August 1896 UK \u2013 [[Bridget Driscoll]] is the first person to die in a petrol-engined car accident, and the first pedestrian victim of an automobile accident in the United Kingdom. As she crossed the grounds of the [[The Crystal Palace|Crystal Palace]] in London, she was struck by an automobile belonging to the [[Anglo-French (automobile)|Anglo-French Motor Carriage Company]] that was being used to give demonstration rides.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/magazine-10987606 | title=How the UK's first fatal car accident unfolded | date=17 August 2010 | accessdate=23 August 2010 | author=Andrew McFarlane | journal=BBC News Magazine }}</ref>\n* 25 February 1899 UK \u2013 [[Edwin Sewell]] and [[Major Richer]] are thrown from their vehicle on [[Harrow on the Hill]], [[Middlesex]], London, and killed. Sewell's death is the first fatality of a driver recorded.\n* 13 September 1899 \u2013 [[Henry H. Bliss]] is the first person killed by a car in the United States.\n\n==1900s==\n* 12 October 1904; First automobile crash (non-fatal) in New Zealand. Auckland, North Island. Capt Subritzky's car collides with a Tramcar in Hobson Street.\n* 12 September 1906; First automobile fatality in New Zealand \u2013 Washdyke, Timaru, South Island. Janet Meikle (Mrs John Meikle) aged 36, died after a crash in a car she was driving.\n* 6 August 1915; Nine year old ''[[RMS Titanic|Titanic]]'' survivor Robert Douglas Spedden is fatally struck by an automobile at his family's winter home in Maine, one of the first car crashes to occur in the state of Maine.\n\n==1920s==\n* 10 June 1925 UK; [[Dibbles Bridge coach crash (1925)|Dibbles Bridge coach crash]]: a tour coach ran away following brake failure and fell off a bridge near [[Hebden, North Yorkshire|Hebden]], [[North Yorkshire]], en route to [[Bolton Abbey]], killing seven passengers.<ref>{{cite news|title=Wheels of Industry|publisher=Commercial Motor|url=http://archive.commercialmotor.com/article/16th-june-1925/4/wheels-of-industry|accessdate=23 August 2014|date=16 June 1925}}</ref>\n\n==1930s==\n\n===1934===\n* July \u2013 A bus crash in Ossining, New York, claimed 20 lives.\n\n===1935===\n* 29 August Belgium \u2013 [[Queen Astrid]] of Belgium is killed in a car crash in [[K\u00fcssnacht am Rigi]], near [[Lake Lucerne]], [[Schwyz]], Switzerland.\n\n===1937===\n* 25 March - A bus carrying a [[roller derby]] team crashed just west of [[Salem, Illinois]], killing 21 of the 23 people on the bus.<ref>http://derbymemoirs.bankedtrack.info/mem_bus.html</ref>\n\n==1940s==\n\n===1941===\n* October UK \u2013 A [[Royal Air Force]] bus crashes into a lorry and catches fire near [[Cheltenham]], [[Gloucestershire]], killing 9 airmen and injuring 13.<ref name=\"chatham\"/>\n\n===1944===\n* June UK \u2013 A [[British Army]] lorry crashes into a house at [[Burley in Wharfedale]], [[Yorkshire]], killing 19 soldiers.<ref name=\"chatham\">\"Twenty-three Cadets Killed by Bus at Chatham\", ''[[The Times]]'', 5 December 1951</ref>\n* October UK \u2013 A [[United States Army]] bus collides with a lorry near [[Marlborough, Wiltshire]], killing 10 soldiers and injuring 21.<ref name=\"chatham\"/>\n\n=== 1947 ===\n* October UK \u2013 A bus crashes into a building at [[Holmfirth]], Yorkshire, killing 9 people.<ref name=\"chatham\"/>\n\n===1948===\n* January UK \u2013 A bus skids into a bus queue at [[Bargeddie]], near [[Glasgow]], Scotland, killing 8 people and injuring 12.<ref name=\"chatham\"/>\n* 24 November Sweden \u2013 A trolleybus on line 96 collided with a truck loaded with concrete slabs that were heading in the opposite direction. The bus drove off [[Essingebron]] in [[Stockholm]] and 11 people died.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://publish.tt-gruppen.com/2014/02/04/ett-riktigt-bildhav/essingebroolyckan-1948/ |publisher=[[Tidningarnas Telegrambyr\u00e5]] |title=Essingebroolyckan 1948 |trans-title=Essinge Bridge accident in 1948 |date=3 February 2014  |access-date=22 March 2016 |language=Swedish}}</ref>\n* 19 December Argentina \u2013 A commuter train hits a truck carrying hikers in the [[Greater Buenos Aires]], killing 44 and injuring 25 others.\n\n==1950s==\n\n===1950===\n\n* 11 February Japan \u2013 A [[Takase, Kumamoto|Takase]]-[[Kumamoto, Kumamoto|Kumamoto]] Ky\u016bsh\u016b Sanko regular route bus plunges into a pond 40 feet below at [[Matsuo, Kumamoto|Matsuo]], [[Kumamoto Prefecture|Kumamoto]], [[Ky\u016bsh\u016b]], Japan, killing 22 people and injuring 18.<ref name=\"natpoljap\">[[National Police Agency (Japan)|National Police Agency]] of Japan</ref>\n* UK (Scotland) May \u2013 A bus and a [[tram]] collide in [[Glasgow]], killing 7 people and injuring 43.<ref name=\"chatham\"/>\n* 7 November Japan \u2013 A regular route bus plunges 240 feet into the Mononobe river, [[Mirabu]], eastern [[K\u014dchi Prefecture]], [[Shikoku]], Japan, killing 33 people; another 24 are injured.<ref name=\"natpoljap\"/>\n\n===1951===\n* 15 July Japan \u2013 A Shimokawai-Chubutenryu regular route bus plunges off the Harada bridge, [[Tenry\u016b River]], [[Urakawa, Hokkaid\u014d]], northwestern [[Shizuoka Prefecture]], killing 24.<ref name=\"natpoljap\"/>\n* 4 December UK \u2013 [[1951 Gillingham bus disaster|Gillingham bus disaster]], [[Gillingham, Kent]], England.<br>During an evening march in a badly-lit area, a bus struck a company of fifty-two young members of the Royal Marines Volunteer Cadet Corps, aged between ten and thirteen years. 24 cadets were killed and 18 injured; at the time it was the greatest loss of life of any road crash in British history. The crash was later ruled accidental.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.bopcris.ac.uk/bopall/ref9265.html| title=Road safety: report: bus accident at Gillingham| author=Braithwaite, J.G.| publisher=Ministry of Transport| year=1952| accessdate=27 June 2007| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927004819/http://www.bopcris.ac.uk/bopall/ref9265.html| archivedate=27 September 2007}}</ref>\n\n===1952===\n* 1 June France \u2013 A bus carrying [[Belgium|Belgian]] tourists crashed through a guard rail of bridge, and plunged into [[Aa River (France)|the Aa River]], [[Gravelines]], [[Nord-Pas-de-Calais]], France. 33 people fatalities. {{Citation needed|date=March 2015}}\n* 4 August United States \u2013 Two Greyhound Lines buses traveling opposite directions on US 81 crash head-on 7 miles south of [[Waco, Texas]], killing 28, including both drivers in the worst commercial bus disaster in American history.\n\n===1954===\n* 29 March. Argentina \u2013 The collision between a train and a bus in the city of [[Coronel Suarez]], [[Buenos Aires Province]] causes 22 dead and 4 injured.\n* 29 September Netherlands \u2013 The brakes and gear box of a Belgian tourist bus fail on the downhill slope of the [[Cauberg]], near [[Valkenburg aan de Geul]]. The uncontrollable vehicle hits a pedestrian, then a monument and a building. 12 people are killed instantly, 7 (including the pedestrian) die in hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvvalkenburg.nl/Busongeluk_1954.3686.0.html|title=Error, Inconel|website=www.tvvalkenburg.nl|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref>\n* 12 November, island of Reunion \u2013 The brakes of a bus fail on the downhill slope of [[Plateau-Caillou]], in [[Saint-Paul, R\u00e9union|Saint-Paul]]. 54 people are killed, 23 instantly.<ref>[[:fr:Accident des rampes de Saint-Paul]]</ref>\n\n===1955===\n* 8 March South Korea \u2013 An overcrowded regular route bus plunged into a bridge and killed at least 38 and injured 17 in [[Osan]], [[Gyeonggi-do]], South Korea. {{Citation needed|date=March 2015}}\n\n===1956===\n* 28 July Finland \u2013 A passenger bus plunges into [[Kallavesi|Lake Kallavesi]] in [[Kuopio]], [[Northern Savonia]], Finland, killing 30 people. It is the worst road crash in [[Finland|Finnish]] history. {{Citation needed|date=March 2015}}\n\n===1957===\n* 6 June United States -<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fayobserver.com/news/20170604/deadliest-crash-in-nc-history-was-right-outside-fayetteville|title=Deadliest crash in NC history was right outside Fayetteville|last=Jacobs|first=Chick|website=The Fayetteville Observer|language=en|access-date=31 January 2019}}</ref> An early morning collision 7 miles north of Fayetteville, North Carolina when a flat bed truck packed with migrant workers pulls in front of a tractor-trailer hauling potatoes, killing 21 people. At the time, it is the worst traffic fatality accident in U.S. history. \n*11 August South Korea \u2013 A bus plunges off a 200-foot cliff in [[Samcheok]], [[Gangwon Province (South Korea)|Gangwon-do]], South Korea. The incident is caused by bus brake failure, killing at least 28 people. {{Citation needed|date=March 2015}}\n* 10 November \u2013 [[1957 Saint-Paul bus accident]]\n\n===1958===\n* 28 February United States \u2013 [[Prestonsburg, Kentucky bus disaster]]: A school bus in [[Floyd County, Kentucky]] hits a wrecker truck and plunges down an embankment into the rain-swollen [[Levisa Fork River]]. The driver and 26 children die in the worst school bus crash in U.S. history. \n* 21 April Colombia \u2013 A bus lost control, plunging into a swollen mountain river, outside of [[Cajamarca]], [[Tolima Department|Tolima]], Colombia, with 40 fatalities. {{Citation needed|date=March 2015}}\n* 22 December Greece \u2013: A suburban bus from [[Ioannina]] to [[Chouliarades]] carrying 34 people (32 passengers, 1 driver, 1 conductor) failed to complete a manoeuvre on the steep road near the village of [[Petrovouni, Ioannina]] and subsequently fell down the 350m slope to [[Arachthos (river)|Arachthos gorge]]. There were 29 fatalities, 7 of them minors.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sirrakiotis.blogspot.com/2011/12/22-1958.html |script-title=el:\u0397 \u03c3\u03c5\u03b3\u03ba\u03bb\u03bf\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u03b1\u03c6\u03ae\u03b3\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7 \u03bc\u03b9\u03b1\u03c2 \u03b3\u03c5\u03bd\u03b1\u03af\u03ba\u03b1\u03c2 \u03c0\u03bf\u03c5 \u03b5\u03c0\u03ad\u03b6\u03b7\u03c3\u03b5 \u03b1\u03c0' \u03c4\u03bf \u03c4\u03c1\u03b1\u03b3\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u03b4\u03c5\u03c3\u03c4\u03cd\u03c7\u03b7\u03bc\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf \u03a4\u03c3\u03af\u03bc\u03c0\u03bf\u03b2\u03bf \u03c3\u03c4\u03b9\u03c2 22 \u0394\u03b5\u03ba\u03ad\u03bc\u03b2\u03c1\u03b7 1958 |trans-title=The shocking narration of a woman that survived the tragic accident at Tsibovo on 22 December 1958 |language=Greek |author=\u0392\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03bb\u03b7\u03c2 \u039a\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03ae\u03c2 |date=22 December 2011|work= |publisher= |accessdate=7 April 2012}}</ref>\n\n===1959===\n* 20 June Germany \u2013 A crowded [[Lauffen bus crash|bus collides with a train]] on a level crossing in [[Lauffen am Neckar]], West Germany killing 45 people, the worst bus accident in German history.<ref name=\"WDR\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wdr.de/themen/panorama/24/busunfall_a14/070619_chronologie.jhtml|title=Chronik: Schwere Busunf\u00e4lle in Deutschland|accessdate=11 August 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081011175200/http://www.wdr.de/themen/panorama/24/busunfall_a14/070619_chronologie.jhtml|archivedate=11 October 2008}}</ref>\n* 10 September United States - Oakland, Maryland:  A school bus from the Garrett County Board of Education stalled out on railroad tracks killing 7 children and injuring 11 <ref> https://historyarchive.wordpress.com/2016/06/23/train-crashes-into-county-school-bus-killing-seven-children/ </ref>\n\n==1960s==\n\n===1960===\n* 24 July \u2013 A charter bus collides with a regular route bus, the charter bus plunging 270 feet into a valley along the toll road of [[Mount Hiei]], [[\u014ctsu, Shiga]], Japan, killing 30 people and injuring another 18.<ref name=\"natpoljap\"/>\n* 14 September \u2013 A truck struck a suburban bus which subsequently crashed on an olive tree between [[Athens]] and [[Korinth]]. The collision claimed 11 lives (10 passengers and the driver).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.car-truck.gr/article.php?ID=381|title=\u0391\u03c0\u03af\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03bf \u0394\u03c5\u03c3\u03c4\u03cd\u03c7\u03b7\u03bc\u03b1/Unbelievable accident|author=\u03a7.\u039a. \u039b\u03b1\u03b6\u03b1\u03c1\u03cc\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2|publisher=Car&Truck|accessdate=8 April 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070812103515/http://www.car-truck.gr/article.php?ID=381|archivedate=12 August 2007}}</ref>\n\n===1961===\n* 14 December. 20 schoolchildren were killed in a bus-train collision two miles east and a mile south of [[Evans, Colorado]]. The bus driver had stopped at the rural track but did not see or hear the train arriving. The bus had almost passed over the track when it was struck by the train.<ref>[http://www.courts.state.co.us/userfiles/file/Court_Probation/19th_Judicial_District/Court_House_History/20%20Children%20Killed%20as%20Passenger%20Train%20Hits%20School%20Bus%20East%20of%20Evans.pdf ''20 Children Killed as Passenger Train Hits School Bus East of Evans''] Greeley Tribune (Colorado); 14 December 1961.</ref>\n\n===1962===\n* 11 June. Argentina \u2013 The [[Villa Soldati level crossing tragedy]] occurred in the city of [[Buenos Aires]] when a train struck a municipal bus carrying school children to kindergarten. There were 42 children killed and another 83 were injured.\n\n===1963===\n* \u2013 7 February \u2013 A bus in [[Northland Region]], New Zealand leaves the road and hits a pole, killing 15 people. This is considered the worst road crash in New Zealand history.<ref>[http://www.teara.govt.nz/1966/D/DisastersAndMishapsRoad/WaitangiDayBusAccident1963/en Waitangi Day Bus Accident, 1963], ''The Encyclopedia of New Zealand 1966''</ref>\n* \u2013 7 April Kenya \u2013 A bus returning from an African church meeting plunges into the Tiva River, [[Mitaboni]], [[Machakos]], Kenya, killing at least 72 people.<ref name=\"kenyaradio\">[[Kenya Broadcasting Corporation]] radio report</ref>\n* \u2013 10 June United States \u2013 An open truck carrying 49 Boy Scouts and leaders stalls while climbing a hill en route to [[Hole in the Rock (rock formation)|Hole in the Rock]], [[Utah]], loses its brakes, and plunges into [https://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&source=s_q&hl=en&geocode=&q=carcass+wash+utah&ie=UTF8&t=k&ll=37.336372,-111.071874&spn=0.002222,0.004828&z=18&iwloc=A Carcass Wash], killing 13 people.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://publicsafety.utah.gov/highwaypatrol/history_1969/escalante.html |title=1960 \u2013 1969 / Tragedy at Escalante |publisher=Utah Department of Public Safety |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090511120307/http://publicsafety.utah.gov/highwaypatrol/history_1969/escalante.html |archivedate=11 May 2009 }}</ref>\n* \u2013 17 September United States \u2013 [[1963 Chualar bus crash|Chualar bus crash]] a train hit a flatbed truck used as a bus at a rail crossing in [[Chualar, California]], killing 32 people and injuring 25 others. It is considered the worst road crash in U.S. history.<ref name=\"Flores\">{{cite journal | title=A Town Full of Dead Mexicans: The Salinas Valley Bracero Tragedy of 1963, the End of the Bracero Program, and the Evolution of California's Chicano Movement | author=Flores, Lori A. | journal=The Western Historical Quarterly |date=Summer 2013  | volume=44 | issue=2 | pages=124\u2013143 | doi=10.2307/westhistquar.44.2.0124}}</ref>\n\n=== 1965 ===\n* 1 January Peru \u2013 A [[Huancayo]]-[[Ayacucho]] regular route bus plunges 300 feet into a ravine of the [[Mantaro River]], Peru, killing 31 people.<ref>The Derrick (Oil City, Pennsylvania via AP; 4 January 1965; p. 2 (available through newspaperarchive.com)</ref>\n* 10 January Mexico \u2013 A bus carrying [[Zona Centro]] soccer players and their families plunges 450 feet into a ravine on the outskirts of [[Dolores Hidalgo]], [[Guanajuato]], Mexico, killing 19 people and injuring 22.<ref name=\"notimex\">[[Notimex]] news agency</ref>\n* 3 February Mexico \u2013 A regular route bus plunges 300 feet off a cliff along the Mexico-[[Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez]] expressway on the outskirts of [[Zacatecas]], Mexico, killing 25 people and injuring 40.<ref name=\"televisa\">[[Televisa]] news report</ref>\n* 10 February Egypt \u2013 A truck carrying 66 people plunged into a canal on the outskirts of al-Ayyat, Egypt, killing 36 people. The truck driver is arrested on suspicion of driving without a license.<ref>Cumberland Evening Times (Maryland) via UP; 11 February 1965; p. 2 (available at newspaperarchive.com)</ref>\n* 18 February Italy \u2013 A Naples-[[Salerno]] regular route bus plunges 50 feet into a ravine on the Naples-[[Pompeii]] expressway near [[Mount Vesuvius]], Italy, killing 17 people and injuring 60.<ref name=\"ansa\">[[Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata|ANSA]] news agency</ref>\n* 2 March Austria \u2013 12 Swedish schoolchildren and 2 Finnish girls on winter sports holiday were killed when the bus they were traveling in was swept away in an avalanche in [[Obertauern]], [[Austria]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.expressen.se/nyheter/dokument/de-dog-i-lavinen--pa-sportlovsresan/ |newspaper=[[Expressen]] |title=De dog i lavinen \u2013 p\u00e5 sportlovsresan |trans-title=They died in the avalanche \u2013 on the winter holiday |first=Knut-G\u00f6ran |last=K\u00e4llberg |date=26 February 2015 |access-date=26 August 2015 |language=Swedish}}</ref>\n* 1 November Egypt \u2013 A crowded trolley bus plunges into the [[Nile]] on the outskirts of [[Dokki]], [[Giza]], Egypt, killing 74 people.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timelines.ws/countries/EGYPT_A.HTML|title=Timeline Egypt|first=Algis|last=Ratnikas|publisher=|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref>\n* 6 December Togo \u2013 Two trucks carrying United Nations Peace Keeping Force workers collide at [[Sotouboua]], Togo. Togolese authorities claim 125 people <!-- not 115 --> are killed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.historyorb.com/today/search.php?day=6&month=December&year=All+Years&e=1&start=0|title=Historical Events on December 6|publisher=|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n===1966===\n* 25 July Germany \u2013 A bus carrying Belgian children from vacation plunges off a [[West Germany|West German]] [[autobahn]] bridge and crashes on its roof. 33 people are killed, including 27 children and the bus driver who fell asleep behind the wheel. Only 4 people survive.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gva.be/dossiers/-e/eeuw/1966/1966_13.html|title=Een eeuw in beeld \u2013 1966|accessdate=11 August 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120210085917/http://www.gva.be/dossiers/-e/eeuw/1966/1966_13.html|archivedate=10 February 2012}}</ref>\n* 7 October Canada \u2013 [[Dorion level crossing accident|Dorion level crossing crash]]: 19 people are killed when a school bus is hit by a CN train in [[Vaudreuil-Dorion, Quebec|Vaudreuil-Dorion]], [[Quebec]].\n\n===1967===\n* 13 September Brazil \u2013 A bus falls from Almas Bridge, near [[Belo Horizonte]], killing 14 people.\n* 15 December United States \u2013 [[Silver Bridge]] collapses under heavy traffic in [[Point Pleasant, West Virginia]], killing 46 people.<ref name=\"bridgefail\">{{cite journal\n | author = Seim, Charles\n |date=May 2008\n | title = '''Why Bridge Have Failed Throughout History'''\n | journal = Civil Engineering\n | volume = 78\n | issue = 5\n | pages = 64\u201371, 84\u201387\n | url = http://www.ASCE.org\n }}\n</ref>\n\n===1968===\n* 6 January UK \u2013 In the [[Hixon rail crash]], a passenger train hits a low-loader transporter and derails killing 11 and injuring 45 in [[Hixon, Staffordshire]], England.<ref name=\"hixonmot\">{{cite book | last=Ministry of Transport | year=1968 | title=Report of the Public Inquiry into the Accident at Hixon Level Crossing on January 6, 1968 | publisher= HMSO | isbn=0-10-137060-1 | url=http://www.railwaysarchive.co.uk/docSummary.php?docID=74 }}</ref>\n* 18 August Japan \u2013 Due to intense rain, two charter buses crash into the [[Hida River]] on national highway route 41 in [[Gero, Gifu|Gero]], [[Gifu Prefecture]], Japan, killing 104 people.<ref name=\"natpoljap\"/>\n\n===1969===\n* 6 June Philippines \u2013 A regular route bus navigating a sharp descending curve on a narrow mountain road near [[Baler, Aurora]], [[Quezon]], Philippines, plunges into a ravine and bursts into flames. 40 people are killed and another 32 are injured.<ref name=\"gmanetwork\">[[GMA Network]] news report</ref>\n* 21 June Syria \u2013 An overcrowded vehicle carrying 35 workers crashes at [[Mahardah]], [[Al-Amam]], killing 25 people.<ref name=\"syrianANA\">[[Syrian Arab News Agency]]</ref>\n* 18 July United States \u2013 The [[Chappaquiddick incident]]. Although only one person ([[Mary Jo Kopechne]]) was killed when a car drove off the Dike Bridge on [[Chappaquiddick Island]], Massachusetts, the crash was notable because the driver was US [[United States Senate|Senator]] [[Ted Kennedy]], and a [[political scandal]] resulted.\n* 2 August Brazil \u2013 A bus fell from Almas Bridge, 30 meters high, near [[Belo Horizonte]], killing 30 people, the second serious crash in the same place, in less than two years.\n\n==1970s==\n\n===1970===\n* 27 September South Korea \u2013 A regular route bus plunges off a mountain cliff on the outskirts of Myongju, [[Gyeongsangnam-do]], killing 15 people and injuring 20.<ref name=\"munhwa\">[[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation]] report</ref>\n* 22 November  Argentina \u2013 A bus plunges into a creek on the outskirts of [[Reconquista, Santa Fe|Reconquista]], [[Santa Fe Province]], killing 56 people and 4 survive .<ref name=\"artear\">[[Artear]] television news report</ref>\n\n===1971===\n* 10 May  South Korea \u2013 A crowded bus plunges off a {{convert|30|ft|m|adj=on}} cliff, crashing into a reservoir on the outskirts of [[Gapyeong|Kapyong]], northeastern [[Gyeonggi-do]], killing 75 people.\n* 10 May Mexico \u2013 Two local buses collide head-on on the Pinotepa National Highway, [[Florencio Villarveal]], [[Guerrero]], Mexico, killing 30 people; another 30 are injured.\n* 5 September South Korea \u2013 A [[Masan]]-[[Jinhae]] regular route bus carrying 30 passengers fell 50-yards from a mountain road on the outskirts of Jinhae, [[Gyeongsangnam-do]], killing 17 people and injuring 16. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 17 September Spain \u2013 A bus carrying Canadian tourists collided head-on with a truck on the outskirts of [[Valdepe\u00f1as]], [[Ciudad Real]], Spain, killing 17 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 5 November  South Korea \u2013 A local bus plunged from a 900 feet-high mountain slope at [[Yeongdo-gu, Busan|Yeongdo-gu]], [[Busan]], killing 26 people and injuring 30. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 8 November Thailand \u2013 A local bus collided head-on with a truck on the outskirts of [[Korat]], [[Nakhon Ratchasima]], killing 27 people and injuring 20. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 18 December Egypt \u2013 A trailer truck carrying local workers plunged into an irrigation canal on the outskirts of [[Aswan]], killing 50 people.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\n===1972===\n* 15 February Philippines \u2013 A [[Batangas]]-[[Manila]] Laguna transit bus collided with a truck, and plunged off the road at Calamba, [[Laguna, Philippines]], in an incident caused by exceed speed, killing 13 people; another 41 are injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 18 February Egypt \u2013 A crowded bus carrying 90 students overturns and plunges into an irrigation canal at [[Banha]], [[Kafr Saad]], Egypt, killing 77 people.\n* 22 March United States \u2013 In [[Congers, New York]] on Gilchrest Road, five Nyack High School students are killed and 44 injured when [[Gilchrest Road, New York crossing accident|a train hits a school bus]] that failed to stop at a crossing. This incident caused New York State to require school vehicles to stop at all railroad crossings.\n* 25 August Netherlands \u2013 In a sudden dense fog on highway [[A16 motorway (Netherlands)|A16]] near [[Prinsenbeek]], many cars and trucks collide. 13 lives are lost in the crash and subsequent fires.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zero-meridean.nl/ramp_sel.html#25aug72|title=Kettingbotsing A16, Prinsenbeek|publisher=|accessdate=1 October 2014}}</ref> After this crash, a fog warning system was installed along the route. Nevertheless, some 18 years later a similar crash occurred.\n* 23 September Japan \u2013 According to the [[National Police Agency (Japan)|National Police Agency]] of Japan and Japanese [[Fuji Television]], an [[Akakura]]-[[Togakushi, Nagano|Togakushi]] regular route bus carrying 82 passengers plunged into a ravine at [[Shinano, Nagano]], Japan. The NPA reports that this road is single lane. 15 people are killed, and another 67 are injured.<ref name=\"natpoljap\"/>\n\n===1973===\n* 1 January Chile \u2013 A bus carrying the Condor soccer club of [[Curic\u00f3]] players and fans skidded on an acute curve and plunged into the [[Chimbarongo River]], on the outskirts of [[San Fernando, Chile|San Fernando]], [[Colchagua Province]], Chile. The bus was returning from a Chilean soccer league second division match; 35 people were killed in the crash. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 22 June Brazil \u2013 A bus skidded on an acute curve on highway [[BR-040]] and plunged into the [[Paraibuna River (Minas Gerais)|Paraibuna River]], killing 25 people.\n* 18 July France \u2013 A bus carrying Belgian tourists plunges into a ravine in [[Vizille]], France, killing 43 people.<ref name=\"QUID\">{{cite web|url=http://www.quid.fr/2007/Transports_Divers/Accidents_De_La_Route/1|title=Accidents de la route|accessdate=11 August 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070819194335/http://www.quid.fr/2007/Transports_Divers/Accidents_De_La_Route/1|archivedate=19 August 2007}}</ref>\n* 22 July Hong Kong \u2013 A bus plunged off the road down a 90m high hillside at the junction between [[Sam Wat Road]] and [[Keung Shan Road]], [[Lantau]], killing 17 and injuring 23.\n* 13 October India \u2013 A regular route bus plunged off a bridge on the outskirts of [[Hazaribagh]], [[Bihar]], India, killing 74 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 10 November Thailand \u2013 A truck carrying 60 workers plunged off a steep road on the outskirts of [[Doi Inthanon]], [[Chiang Mai]], Thailand, killing 40 people and injuring 20. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\n===1974===\n* 15 January \u2013 [[1974 Blythe, California bus crash]]: A bus carrying farm laborers missed a ninety-degree turn on an intersection and fell into a drainage canal near [[Blythe, California]], killing 19. \n* 28 July \u2013 A crowded bus and a truck collide near [[Bel\u00e9m]], Brazil, killing 69 people.<ref name=\"QUID\" />\n* 30 July - United States: A 1972 Oldsmobile station wagon, occupied by four children and four adults, collided with a Soo Line freight train at the Fibre Crossing in Fibre, Michigan, which did not have lights or gates installed.\n* 8 September Argentina \u2013 A bus returning from religious pilgrimage ran off a road and plunged 750 feet into a canyon on the outskirts of [[Salta Province]], Argentina, killing 35 people.\n\n===1975===\n* 1 January Japan \u2013 A charter bus carrying 62 passengers plunged 100 feet into Aoki Lake, [[\u014cmachi, Nagano|Omachi]], [[Nagano, Nagano|Nagano]], Japan, killing 24 people.<ref name=\"natpoljap\"/>\n* 1 March Kenya \u2013 An explosion in a  [[Nairobi]]-[[Mombasa]] regular route bus in downtown Nairobi, Kenya, was blamed on Kenyan People Liberation Front, a terrorist group. 26 people killed, another 60 injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 2 April France \u2013 A bus carrying French pilgrims plunged 120 feet into the [[Ramache River]] along the highway N85, at the end of [[Rampe de Laffrey]], [[Vizille]], [[Rh\u00f4ne-Alpes]], France, killing 28 people, and injuring 17. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 20 April Italy \u2013 At least 27 vehicles crashed within 15 minutes on the [[Naples]]-[[Caserta]] expressway Autostrada del Sole on the outskirts of Naples, Italy, killing 11 people and injuring 53. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 27 May UK \u2013 [[Dibbles Bridge Coach Crash]], England: a bus full of pensioners falls off a bridge near [[Hebden, North Yorkshire|Hebden]], [[North Yorkshire]] killing 32 people, and injuring 13.<ref>{{ cite web\n|url=http://www.hse.gov.uk/research/rrpdf/rr073.pdf\n|title=Transport fatal accidents and FN-curves:1967\u20132001\n|publisher=Health and Safety Executive\n|accessdate=20 November 2011}}</ref>\n* 15 June Austria \u2013 A bus carrying elderly tourists plunged 120 feet into a ravine on the outskirts of [[Villach]], [[Carinthia (state)|Carinthia]], Austria, killing 21 people and injuring 23. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 29 July Mexico \u2013 A bus carrying religious pilgrims plunged 200 feet down the side of mountain before coming to rest. The crash was at Chalma, [[Veracruz]], Mexico, killing 18 people and injuring 30. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 13 September \u2013 A crowded bus plunges off a cliff in Costa Rica, killing 48 people.\n\n===1976===\n* 16 February Sweden \u2013 The worst traffic accident in Sweden occurred outside [[Axamo]], [[J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping]]. Overheated tires caused a bus fire, killing 15 and injured 28.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.gp.se/nyheter/sverige/1.184052-tidigare-svara-bussolyckor |newspaper=[[G\u00f6teborgs-Posten]] |title=Tidigare sv\u00e5ra bussolyckor |trans-title=Past accidents involving buses |date=22 September 2009 |access-date=22 March 2016 |language=Swedish}}</ref>\n* 10 March \u2013 A regular route bus lost control due to brake failure and plunged down a mountain side in central [[Escuintla]], Guatemala, killing 38 people; another 14 are injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 21 May United States \u2013 [[Yuba City bus disaster]] A bus carrying the [[Yuba City High School]] [[a cappella]] choir falls off [[Interstate 680 (California)|Interstate 680]] in [[California]], killing 28 students and a teacher. This is the second deadliest bus crash in U.S. history, after the 1963 Chualar bus crash.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timelines.ws/20thcent/1976.HTML|title=Timeline 1976|publisher=|accessdate=1 October 2014}}</ref>\n* 22 August Brazil \u2013 Former president [[Juscelino Kubitschek]] is killed when his car lost control and crashes against a truck on the [[Dutra Highway]]. His driver is also killed.\n* 31 October Indonesia \u2013 A tourist bus head-on collides with a mini bus at outskirt of [[Bogor]], [[West Java]], Indonesia, in an incident caused when the tourist bus has brake failure, killing 34 people and injuring 25. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 14 November Brazil \u2013 A bus carrying municipal election candidate and supporters has plunged into river near ferry terminal at [[Manaus]]-Itacoatiara expressway, [[Uruara]], [[Par\u00e1]], Brazil, killing 38 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 15 November \u2013 A bus swept by flash flood in Tsoaing River, Thaba Pechela, [[Mafeteng]], Lesotho, killing at least 90 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 21 December France \u2013 A school bus carrying mentally handicapped children returning from a class in making [[Christmas ornament]]s at the [[\u00c9douard S\u00e9guin]] Children Medical Center, plunged into the River [[Rhone]], on the outskirts of [[Lyon]], France, with at least 13 people killed.<ref>''13 Retarded Children Die In French Bus Plunge''; Kingsport Times (Tennessee); 22 December 1976; p. 2 (available at newspaperarchive.com)</ref>\n\n===1977===\n* 3 April Egypt \u2013 A crowded bus skidded off the road, and plunged into irrigation [[Kassed Canal]] where it is parallel to the road at the outskirt of [[Tanta]], [[Nile Delta]], Egypt, killing 19 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 9 June \u2013 A truck crashes into a crowd at a downtown Moscow bus stop, killing eight people and injuring 18.<ref name=\"oberg\">Oberg, James E. ''Uncovering Soviet Disasters: Exploring the Limits of Glasnost.'' New York: Random House, 1988: 106.</ref>\n* 7 July Pakistan. A bus carrying 44 cadets of Pakistan Military Academy, on an excursion, skidded off the road plunging into a 1000&nbsp;ft deep ravine, near Nathiagali, killing 16 cadets including a Saudi cadet. 28 Cadets were injured.\n* 11 August Japan \u2013 According to the Japanese National Police Agency and [[NHK]] television, a charter bus plunged 120 feet into a ravine at Nagatoro bridge, [[K\u014dfu, Yamanashi|Kofu]], [[Yamanashi Prefecture]], Japan, killing 11 people; another 39 are injured.<ref name=\"natpoljap\"/>\n\n===1978===\n*1 January Thailand \u2013 A truck carrying many passengers collided head-on with a bus on the outskirts of Nong Bua Daeng, [[Chaiyaphum]], Thailand, killing 25 people; another 86 are injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n*3 January Colombia \u2013 A [[Villavicencio]]-[[Bogot\u00e1]] regular route bus plunged 130 feet off a cliff on the outskirts of [[Quetame]], [[Eastern Province, Cundinamarca|Oriente]], Colombia, killing 30 people; another 16 are injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 22 January Poland \u2013 A truck with steel elements collided with crowded bus of PKS (Polish Road Transport) \u2013 killed 15 people and seriously injured 14.<ref>[[:pl:Katastrofa autobusu ko\u0142o Osiecznicy]]</ref>\n*9 March Brazil \u2013 A [[Bras\u00edlia]]-S\u00e3o Paulo regular route bus collided with a gasoline tank truck on the Faria Lima expressway near [[Barretos]] in the state of [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], Brazil. The bus driver swerved and lost control, and the vehicle burst into flames, killing 19. Another five are injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n*11 July Spain \u2013 [[Los Alfaques Disaster]]: in [[Sant Carles de la R\u00e0pita]], a [[tank truck]] containing 45 m\u00b3 of [[Liquefied petroleum gas|liquefied propylene]] leaves the road and veers into the Los Alfaques camping site after colliding with a building. The resulting [[BLEVE|fire ball]] is more than 100 meters in diameter and kills at least 215 people (some sources speak of 216 or even 270), and injures 200 people.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unizar.es/guiar/1/Accident/Alfaques.htm|title=Accidente de Los Alfaques (San Carlos de la R\u00e0pita, Espa\u00f1a)|publisher=|accessdate=1 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060705211825/http://www.unizar.es/guiar/1/Accident/Alfaques.htm|archive-date=5 July 2006|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* 4 August Canada \u2013 A bus carrying mentally handicapped people plunges into a lake in [[Eastman, Quebec]], Canada killing 40 people. Only seven people survive.<ref>{{in lang|fr}} [http://www.historiatv.com/emission/tragedies/1646639/ Catastrophes Sur Les Routes] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070811125644/http://www.historiatv.com/emission/tragedies/1646639/ |date=11 August 2007 }}</ref>\n* 15 November Poland \u2013 Two buses of PKS (Polish Road Transport) with miners going to work plunged into the river Jezioro \u017bywieckie near \u017bywiec, killing 30 miners, one woman and two drivers.<ref>[[:pl:Katastrofa autobus\u00f3w ko\u0142o \u017bywca]]</ref>\n\n===1979===\n* 15 January. Argentina \u2013 In the town of [[Castelli, Buenos Aires|Castelli]], [[Buenos Aires Province]] a serious collision between two passenger buses resulted in 33 dead and 54 wounded.\n\n==1980s==\n\n===1980===\n* 12 February Bulgaria \u2013 An [[Ohrid]]-[[\u0130zmir]] regular route bus carrying 50 passengers aboard failed to navigate a curve and plunged into the [[Marica River]] near [[Sofia]], Bulgaria, killing 25 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 18 February Costa Rica \u2013 A 40-passenger bus and an 18-passenger bus collided head-on at [[San Isidro, Heredia Province|San Isidro]], [[Heredia Province]], Costa Rica, killing 16 people, with 39 injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 3 March \u2013 23 people are burned to death when city bus 62 catches fire in [[Minsk]], Belarus after driving into a pool of gasoline spilled from a fuel truck.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mk.by/archiv/28.09.2006/rub7.php|title=Minskiy Kurier article (in Russian)|accessdate=11 August 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928000412/http://mk.by/archiv/28.09.2006/rub7.php|archivedate=28 September 2007}}</ref>\n* 5 March India \u2013 A bus slammed into a banyan tree, after attempting to overtake a truck on the outskirts of [[Krishnanagar, Nadia|Krishnanagar]], [[West Bengal]], India. 32 people are killed and 42 injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 9 May United States \u2013 35 people are killed in the [[Sunshine Skyway Bridge#Bridge disaster|Sunshine Skyway Bridge disaster]], [[Tampa, Florida]], after a [[cargo ship]] collided with a bridge [[pier]], demolishing over 1200&nbsp;ft. of the bridge.\n* 28 May Canada \u2013 A bus carrying members of a Canadian Pacific Railway \"steel gang\" near [[Swift Current, Saskatchewan]] was side-swiped by a car, causing it to flip on its side. The bus was then struck by a tanker truck carrying hot asphalt, killing 22 people.{{Citation needed|date=November 2016}}\n* 5 June United States \u2013 A tour bus rolls off the highway near [[Jasper, Arkansas]], killing 22 people and injuring 19.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ntsb.gov/publictn/1981/HAR8101.htm|title=Highway Accident Report HAR-81/01|publisher=|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref>\n* 10 June Ireland; A bus crashes and overturns outside Limerick, Republic of Ireland killing 2 people and injuring dozens more.\n* 25 June India \u2013 A bus carrying 100 passengers lost control and plunged into the [[Rahand Nullah River]], [[Bilaspur, Madhya Pradesh|Bilaspur]], [[Madhya Pradesh]], India, killing 58 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 29 June Pakistan \u2013 According to the [[Associated Press of Pakistan]], a bus carrying more than 100 women and children plunges into a canal in Upper Jhelam, near [[Mirpur, Pakistan|Mirpur]], Kashmir of Pakistan, and at least 90 people drown as a result.<ref name=\"slate\">Shafer, Jack. \"The Rise and Fall of the \"Bus Plunge\" Story: What Killed This Former ''The New York Times'' Staple? http://www.slate.com/id/2152895\" ''Slate.com'' 13 November 2006</ref>\n* 29 June Romania \u2013 a bus carrying 83 people went off a bridge and overturned into a deep marsh near Hu\u0163ani, a village in [[Vl\u0103deni, Boto\u015fani|Vl\u0103deni]] [[commune]], [[Boto\u015fani County]], killing 48 people and injuring 35.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.monitorulbt.ro/Reportaj/2010-06-29/30+de+ani+de+la+cel+mai+cumplit+accident|title=30 de ani de la cel mai cumplit accident|publisher=|accessdate=1 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100705051534/http://www.monitorulbt.ro/Reportaj/2010-06-29/30+de+ani+de+la+cel+mai+cumplit+accident|archive-date=5 July 2010|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* 11 November Egypt \u2013 A bus collided with two trucks, then plunged into an irrigation canal near [[Beni Suef]], Egypt, killing 30 people and injuring at least 30. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 25 November India \u2013 A [[Gwalior]]-[[Delhi]] Delhi Transport bus tumbled into the [[Chambal River]], [[Dholpur]], [[Rajasthan]], India, killing 40 people and injuring 30. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\n===1981===\n\n* 3 January India \u2013 A passenger bus skidded and plunged 200-feet down into a ravine at outskirt of [[Galhar]], Indian state of Kashmir, killing 17 people and injuring 18. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 12 February Venezuela \u2013 A crowded bus, heavy truck, a small vehicle and many vehicles collide at [[Barquisimeto]], Venezuela, killing 36 people and injuring 31. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 14 April India \u2013 A bus carrying Hindu pilgrims swerved to the left of the road, and navigating a turn with brakes failed, caught fire at [[Srisailam]], [[Andhra Pradesh]], India, killing 61 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 7 July India \u2013 A bus skidded off the road and plunged into a deep gorge at outskirt of [[Kawanpui]], [[Mizoram]], India, killing 32 people and injuring 19. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 14 June Pakistan \u2013 A bus plunged 300-feet into a ravine at [[Kohat Pass]], [[Kohat]], Pakistan, killing 23 people and injuring 25. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 12 August India \u2013 An Uttar Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation regular route bus plunged into a 450-feet deep ravine along a mountain road in Pithorgarh, [[Uttar Pradesh]], India, killing 43 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 9 September Brazil \u2013 A truck rammed a bus on an acute curve and forced it over a 330-foot cliff near [[Santos, S\u00e3o Paulo|Santos]], state of [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], Brazil, killing 29 people and injuring 14. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 29 September Spain \u2013 A head-on collision of a bus and a truck in [[Toledo (province)|Toledo]] province, Spain, kills at least 25 people.<ref>Associated Press. \"[https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9E02E0DF1539F93AA1575AC0A967948260&sec=&pagewanted=print Bus Crash Kills 25 in Spain]\" ''The New York Times'' 29 September 1981</ref>\n* 14 October India \u2013 A public bus plunged into foothills at outskirt of [[Shimla|Simla]], [[Himachal Pradesh]], India, killing 40 people and injuring 45. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\n===1982===\n* 21 January Bangladesh \u2013 An overcrowded bus swerves to avoid a speeding truck and plunges nine meters off a bridge at [[Narayanganj]], [[Isa Khan]], Bangladesh, killing at least 28 people; another 40 are injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 31 January Chile \u2013 Two buses collide and plunge into a [[gorge]] on the outskirts of [[Santiago, Chile]], killing 14 people and injuring 70.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9C00EFD61338F932A05752C0A964948260|title=Reuters report via New York Times|date=31 January 1982|publisher=|accessdate=15 November 2014}}</ref>\n* 27 March Mexico \u2013 A [[Toluca]]-[[Mexico City]] Passenger bus head-on collided with a trailer truck at outskirt of Mexico City, in an incident caused by condition of rain with narrow road, at least twenty-eight people dead and injuring 32. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 1 August France \u2013 Two buses carrying children collide with cars and burst into flames in [[Beaune]], France, killing 53 people, including 44 children. Worst highway crash in France.<ref>[https://www.humanite.fr/2002-08-01_Societe_-Route-Il-y-a-vingt-ans-l-accident-de-Beaune Il ya vingt ans, l'accident de Beaune] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090804100900/http://www.humanite.fr/2002-08-01_Societe_-Route-Il-y-a-vingt-ans-l-accident-de-Beaune |date=4 August 2009 }}</ref> Full article: ''[[Beaune coach crash]]''.\n* 12 August Mexico - During the early hours of the day, a Porsche car collides with a truck, propelling the Porsche to crash into an oncoming [[Dina Torton]] truck, killing the driver of the Porsche car, world champion boxer [[Salvador Sanchez]].<ref>http://izquierdazo.com/la-madrugada-tragica-de-salvador-sanchez/3008</ref>\n* 9 September \u2013 An express train collided with a bus at outskirt of [[Sz\u00e9kesfeh\u00e9rv\u00e1r]], [[Fej\u00e9r County]], Hungary, killing at least sixteen passengers. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 12 September \u2013 A bus carrying German tourists collides with a train on a level crossing near [[Z\u00fcrich]], Switzerland, killing 39 people. The barriers were not closed, because the operator pressed a wrong button. Only two passengers survive the crash. It is the worst road crash in Switzerland to date.<ref name=\"ADAC\">{{cite web|url=http://www.adac.de/Tests/Mobilitaet_und_Reise/Busreisen/bustest_2004/busunfaelle_europa/default.asp?TL=2|title=Busunf\u00e4lle in Europa seit 1982|author=ADAC|accessdate=1 October 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930023621/http://www.adac.de/Tests/Mobilitaet_und_Reise/Busreisen/bustest_2004/busunfaelle_europa/default.asp?TL=2|archivedate=30 September 2007}}</ref>\n* 13 September Monaco \u2013 [[Grace Kelly|Grace, Princess of Monaco]] drove her Rover P6 off of a serpentine roadway and down a mountainside, perhaps after suffering a stroke. She died the next day.\n* 3 November \u2013 Hundreds are allegedly killed in the [[Salang tunnel fire]] in central Afghanistan, after a disaster involving a Soviet fuel convoy. Estimates are as great as 2,700 dead.{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n* 26 December \u2013 A passenger bus plunged into a river at Brahmanbari, Bangladesh, at least forty-five people dead and eighty injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\n=== 1983 ===\n* 19 January United States \u2013 A [[semi-trailer truck]] crashed into a mainline toll booth on the [[Connecticut Turnpike]] in [[Stratford, Connecticut]], after brake failure, killing six people and injuring four.<ref>{{cite news |first= |last= |coauthors= |title=6 Die in Crash at Toll Station in Connecticut |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1983/01/20/nyregion/6-die-in-crash-at-toll-station-in-connecticut.html |work=[[New York Times]] |publisher= |date=20 January 1983 |accessdate=15 October 2010 }}</ref>\n* 11 February \u2013 A [[Salonica]]-[[Athens]] express bus head-on collided with a truck at outskirt of [[Amfikleia]], [[Phthiotis]], Greece, in an incident caused by both vehicles exceeding the speed limit, killing seventeen people and injuring ten. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 13 February \u2013 A passenger bus head-on collided with a truck, when driver trying to pass a car at outskirt of [[\u015eanl\u0131urfa]], Turkey, killing twenty people and injuring ten. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 2 March \u2013 A charter bus plunged off mountainous highway into [[Mantaro River]], [[Jauja]], [[Jun\u00edn Region]], Peru, killing thirty people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 1 November \u2013 A bus collides with a [[motorcycle]] and hits a second bus 370 miles northeast of [[Bangkok]], Thailand, killing 21 people and injuring 40.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9C06EED71639F932A35752C1A965948260|title=UPI report via New York Times|date=1 November 1983|publisher=|accessdate=15 November 2014}}</ref>\n* 4 December \u2013 A regular route bus crashed into a utility pole and caught fire on the outskirts of [[Bogot\u00e1]], Colombia, in an incident caused by technical problems and excessive speed, killing 21 people. Another five people are injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\n=== 1984 ===\n\n* 30 January India \u2013 A [[Paonta Sahib]]-[[Nangai]] regular route bus plunged 14 feet into a canal and sank at the Sarsa Bridge on the outskirts of [[Rapar]], [[Punjab (India)|Punjab]] of India, killing 80 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 4 May India \u2013 An APSRTC bus carrying around 40 people plunged with a truck head on. The crash happened near Kavali of Andhra Pradesh, India, killed 20 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 1 August India \u2013 A bus carrying local government employees plunged into a canal after its right front tire burst. The crash, on the outskirts of [[Ingraj Bazar]], [[West Bengal]], India, killed 40 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 1 August \u2013 A bus skidded on a wet road, lost control and plunged into the [[Indus River]] on the Karakoram Highway, [[Baiji Sharif]], northern Pakistan, killing 27 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 26 August \u2013 A bus slipped and plunged into a 13-feet deep irrigation canal near [[Salkot]], Nepal, killing 25 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 5 September \u2013 A bus carrying 50 passengers plunged into a {{convert|3300|ft|m|adj=mid|-deep}} gorge near [[Shillong]], [[Meghalaya]], India, in an incident caused by the driver losing control on an acute curve with dense fog. 29 people are killed, and another 25 are injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 24 September \u2013 A bus plunges into a gorge in [[Uttar Pradesh]], India, killing 42 people and injuring 15.<ref>Associated Press \"[https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9501E1DD143BF937A1575AC0A962948260&pagewanted=print Bus Crash in India Kills 34]\" ''The New York Times'' 14 September 1992</ref>\n* 31 October. Argentina \u2013 The collision of a commuter train with a passenger bus during the morning hours in the city of [[Buenos Aires]] causes a tragedy, 48 people die and 15 others injured. It is the worst crash involving a train and a bus in Argentina.\n* 25 November \u2013 A bus returning from the shore of the Black Sea collided with a lorry in dense fog at northern [[Cankiri]], Turkey, at least thirty people dead and injuring twenty-four. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 23 December \u2013 An overcrowded passenger bus plunged off an expressway at Apaseo Grande, Guanjuato, Mexico, at least twenty-two people dead and injuring thirty-five. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 24 December \u2013 An overcrowded bus with ninety passengers skidded off a steep bank on Wapadsberg Mountain, Craddock-Graaff Region, [[Eastern Cape]], South Africa, at least 42 people dead and injuring 25. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\n===1985===\n* 11 January \u2013 A regular route bus skidded off a covered bridge in icy conditions and plunged into a frozen river at [[Yeongdong County|Yeongdong]], [[Chungcheongbuk-do]], South Korea, killing 38 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 28 January \u2013 A bus carrying skiers plunges into a reservoir in [[Nagano, Nagano|Nagano]], Japan killing 25 people.\n* 27 March \u2013 A school bus crashed through a barrier and plunged into a dam killing 42 school children [[Westdene]], [[Gauteng]],  South Africa. It is known as the [[Westdene dam disaster]]\n* 6 April \u2013 A regular route bus suffered brake failure and plunged 20 feet at [[Bherughat]], Madhy Pradesh, India, killing 16 people and injuring 39.  {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 20 April \u2013 A bus plunged 500 feet down the side of road at outskirt of [[Hibberdene, KwaZulu-Natal|Hibberdene]], [[KwaZulu-Natal|Natal]], South Africa, killing 18, another injuring are 29. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 11 June \u2013 A bus carrying school children on a field trip collides with a train near [[Moshav]] [[HaBonim, Israel|Habonim]], Israel; 21 people killed, including 19 children.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://crazycrashes.wordpress.com/train-wreck-historical-timeline-1950-to-2000/ |title=train wreck historical timeline 1950-to-2000 |publisher=crazycrashes.wordpress.com}}</ref>\n* 21 July \u2013 A bus carrying 42 passengers returning from a Buddhist ordination ceremony collided head-on with a truck at an intersection in a suburb of [[Bangkok]], Thailand, killing 26 people and injuring 16. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 21 July \u2013 A bus overturned after brake failure and ran through a crowded market at Halsema expressway, [[Atok, Benguet|Atok]], [[Benguet]], Philippines, killing 28 people and injuring 70. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 22 September \u2013 A school bus rolls over in [[Layyah]], Pakistan, killing 30 children.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9505E2DC1439F931A1575AC0A963948260|title=Brief New York Times Report|date=22 September 1985|publisher=|accessdate=15 November 2014}}</ref>\n* 21 October UK \u2013 A [[Coach (vehicle)|coach]] collides with stationary traffic due to construction work on the [[M6 motorway]], in Lancashire between [[City of Preston, Lancashire|Preston]] and [[Lancaster, Lancashire|Lancaster]], killing 13 people.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://newspapers.umsystem.edu/default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?BaseHRef=CMN/1985/10/22&EntityId=Ar01202&Skin=Google&ViewMode=GIF|title=Columbia Missourian 22nd October 1985|publisher=|accessdate=11 August 2017}}{{dead link|date=September 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n* 21 December \u2013 A [[S\u00e3o Paulo]]-[[Rio de Janeiro]] Cometa Transport bus veered off the road and into Guandu River, outskirt of [[Pira\u00ed]], Rio state, Brazil, killing 22 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\n===1986===\n* 17 January India \u2013 A crowded passenger bus plunged into an 89-foot-deep ravine while navigating a sharp curve at [[Navsari]], [[Gujarat]], India, killing 49 people and injuring ten. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 26 April India \u2013 A bus carrying pilgrims to a shrine where plunged off a cliff at outskirt of [[Kathgodam]], [[Uttarakhand]], India, killing 44 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 12 May South Africa \u2013 An overcrowded bus ran out of control due to brake failure and flipped over near [[Mount Frere, Eastern Cape]], [[Transkei]], South Africa, killing 30 people. Another 64 people are injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 23 May, [[Philippines]] \u2013 A bus falls off a cliff and explodes in [[Antique Province]], killing 23 people and injuring 15.<ref>Associated Press. \"[https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9A0DE6DE153DF936A15756C0A960948260&sec=&pagewanted=print  Philippine Bus Crash Kills 23]\" ''The New York Times'' 25 May 1986</ref>\n* 30 May United States \u2013 A tour bus plunges into the [[West Walker River]] near [[Walker, Mono County, California]], killing 21 people and injuring 19.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ntsb.gov/publictn/1987/HAR8704.htm|title=Highway Accident Report HAR-87-4|publisher=|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref>\n* 17 June Peru \u2013 A bus carrying 40 passengers, including school children, plunged off a highway and into an irrigation ditch near [[San Vicente de Ca\u00f1ete|Canete]], Peru, killing 19 people and injuring 17. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 22 June China \u2013 Two buses carrying Baobaoshan rural factory workers plunged 800-feet before an acute curve in the [[Mount Wutai]] area, [[Shanxi]], China, killing 31 people and injuring 35. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 26 July UK \u2013 [[Lockington rail crash]]: A train derails after colliding with a [[Ford Escort (Europe)|Ford Escort]] at a rail crossing in [[Lockington, East Riding of Yorkshire|Lockington]], Yorkshire, England, killing 8 people aboard the train and one aboard the car.\n* 27 September Sweden \u2013 [[Metallica]]'s bus skids off the road, killing [[Cliff Burton]].<ref name=\"JFA\">{{cite book| last = McIver | first = Joel | authorlink = Joel McIver| title = Justice for All: The Truth about Metallica | publisher = Omnibus Press| year = 2004 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/justiceforalltru0000mciv_h8q4/page/159 159]\u2013165| url = https://archive.org/details/justiceforalltru0000mciv_h8q4| url-access = registration | quote = cliff burton death. | isbn = 978-0-7119-9600-7}}\n</ref> \n* 8 October Taiwan \u2013 A tourist bus plunges 33-yards down a valley onto a river bank at East-West Cross Island Expressway, outskirt of [[Taichung]], Taiwan, killing 39 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 21 October \u2013 Two packed buses hit by a passenger express train at [[Landhi]], [[Karachi]], Pakistan, killing 35 people and injuring 24. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 3 November \u2013 A bus crashed into road side at outskirt of [[Murshidabad]], [[West Bengal]], India, killing 33 people and injuring 28. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\n===1987===\n* 4 January Brazil \u2013 A bus carrying workers head-on collided with a truck carrying tomatoes at [[Itapetininga]], state of [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], Brazil, killing fifteen people and injuring eleven. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 21 January Chile \u2013 A truck and a bus collide near [[Temuco]], Chile, killing 44 people.\n* 23 February Nigeria \u2013 A bus carrying a wedding party skidded off an express way at outskirt of [[Nsukka]], [[Anambra State]], Nigeria, killing 35 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 29 March China \u2013 A bus plunges off a cliff in [[Shaanxi]], China, killing 19 people and injuring 28.<ref>Reuters [https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9B0DE5DE1F31F936A35757C0A961948260 Chinese Bus Plunge Kills 19] ''The New York Times'' 5 April 1987</ref>\n* 6 May Thailand \u2013 A bus carrying university students and teachers rammed into the side of a mountain near [[Kanchanaburi]], [[Sri Sawat]], Thailand, killing 20 people and injuring 27. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 7 July Germany \u2013 A tank truck carrying gasoline crashes and hits an ice-cream parlor at [[Herborn (Hesse)|Herborn]], [[Lahn-Dill-Kreis]], [[Hesse]], Germany, killing six people and injuring 29. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 26 July Brazil \u2013 A drunk bus driver crashes his bus against another bus, in highway [[BR-040]], near [[Belo Horizonte]], killing 69 people, the worst road crash to date in Brazil.\n* 30 July India \u2013 A regular route bus crashes into Yanto canal at outskirt of [[Dakpatthar]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], India, killing 39 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 20 October \u2013 A bus veered into a high-voltage power pole and caught fire after colliding with another bus at Al-Kufaytah, Nahr-an-nil, Sudan, killing 64 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 28 October UK \u2013 A diesel [[tank truck]] collides with stationary traffic on the [[M61 motorway]] near [[City of Preston, Lancashire|Preston]], [[Lancashire]], killing 12 people and injuring 6. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 11 December Egypt \u2013 A bus carrying local primary school children returning from the Guiza zoo was smashed by a fast-speed train at an unmarked railroad level crossing at [[Ein Sham]], on the outskirts [[Cairo]], Egypt, killing 62 children and injuring 67.<ref>Associated Press. \"[https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9B0DE7D7123FF931A25751C1A961948260&sec=&pagewanted=print Egypt Bus Crash Kills At Least 57 Children]\" ''The New York Times'' 12 December 1987</ref>\n* 27 December Algeria \u2013 A passenger bus and two trucks carrying illegal passengers collided near Bouandas, [[S\u00e9tif]], Algeria, killing 32 people and injuring 19. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\n===1988===\n* 1 February Haiti \u2013 A truck carrying many hitchhikers was hit by ten-wheel flatbed truck carrying coffee. The truck overturned and plunged into the [[Grande-Anse River]], near [[J\u00e9r\u00e9mie]], [[Grand'Anse (department)|Grand'Anse]], Haiti, killing 70 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 15 February \u2013 A bus plunged into a 170-foot ravine near [[Pallasca Province]], [[Ancash Region]], Peru, killing 14 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 10 April \u2013 An overcrowded regular route bus blew a front tire and plunged into an irrigation canal near [[Amphoe Mueang Chainat|Mueang Chainat]], [[Chainat Province]], Thailand, killing 42 people and injuring 11. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 20 April Thailand \u2013 A local bus collided with a paramilitary troop tank at [[Nakhon Ratchasima]], Thailand.  The resulting explosion killed 25 people and injured nine. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 14 May United States \u2013 27 people die in the [[Carrollton, Kentucky bus collision|Carrollton bus disaster]] near [[Carrollton, Kentucky]], after a collision with a [[drunk driver]] [[driving the wrong way]] on [[Interstate 71]]. It remains the deadliest drunk driving crash in American history.{{citation needed|date=November 2013}}\n* 18 July Brazil \u2013 A [[Londrina]]-[[Campinas]] regular route bus swerved to avoid three cows crossing national road 369, then struck the rear of another bus near [[Cornelio Procopio]], [[Paran\u00e1 (state)|Parana]], Brazil, killing 39 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 12 August Iran \u2013 Two buses collide on the highway between [[Tehran]] and [[Tabriz]] in northern Iran, killing 30 people and injuring 50.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=940DE4DC1031F937A2575BC0A96E948260|title=AP report via New York Times|date=14 August 1988|publisher=|accessdate=15 November 2014}}</ref>\n* 15 August Norway \u2013 16 people, including 12 children, die in the [[M\u00e5b\u00f8dalen bus accident|M\u00e5b\u00f8dalen bus crash]] when a bus rams into a concrete wall in a tunnel 60 miles east of [[Bergen|Bergen, Norway]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://wwwc.aftonbladet.se/nyheter/9808/15/sorg.html |newspaper=[[Aftonbladet]] |title=Sorg g\u00e5r inte \u00f6ver \u2013 men g\u00e5r att leva med |trans-title=Grief does not pass \u2013 but you can live with |first=Kerstin |last=Weigl |date=14 August 1998 |access-date=9 January 2012 |language=Swedish}}</ref>\n* 23 August Austria \u2013 A Hungarian tour bus lost control and slammed into a truck at [[Schwadorf]] near [[Vienna]], Austria, killing 14 people and injuring 11. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 22 September India \u2013 A bus falls into a ravine near [[Shimla|Simla]], India. 35 people die.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=940DE4DB1031F932A15751C0A96E948260|title=Brief New York Times Report|date=21 February 1988|publisher=|accessdate=15 November 2014}}</ref>\n* 25 September India \u2013 A bus plunged into Bhakra canal, smashing through the safety railing of a bridge near [[Jogwala]], [[Sangrur district]], [[Punjab (India)|Punjab]], India, killing 67 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 6 October \u2013 A Kafr el Sheikh-[[Baltim]] regular-route bus was hit by a flatbed trailer on the outskirts of [[El-Mahalla El-Kubra]], Egypt, killing 28 people and injuring 21. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 9 October \u2013 A [[Guwahati]]-[[Nalbari]] regular-route bus skidded off a road and crashed into a flooded pond on the outskirts of [[Guwahati]], [[Assam]], India, killing 50 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 12 October \u2013 A bus ignites after toppling into a ditch in [[Shaanxi]], China, killing 43 people and injuring 40.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=940DE1DA1539F934A25753C1A96E948260&sec=&pagewanted=print|title=AP report via New York Times|date=17 October 1988|publisher=|accessdate=15 November 2014}}</ref>\n* 21 October \u2013 Three separate buses collided with a refrigerator truck and overturned at [[Martorell]], [[Catalonia]], Spain, killing 14 people and injuring 65. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\n===1989===\n* 17 January Sri Lanka \u2013 51 people die and 110 are injured when a bus packed with school children collides with a train at a level crossing of Ahungalle, southern Sri Lanka.\n* 24 February \u2013 A [[Salvador, Bahia|Bahia]]-[[Bras\u00edlia]] regular route bus head-on collided with a truck carrying a load of corn at outskirt of [[Catal\u00e3o]], [[Goi\u00e1s]], Brazil, killing 16 people and injuring 25. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 26 February \u2013 A bus plunged 330-feet into a deep valley at outskirt of Taoyuan City (now [[Taoyuan District]]), Taiwan, killing twelve people and injuring 24. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 19 May \u2013 A [[Lima]]-[[Huancayo]] regular route bus carrying sixty passengers slammed on brakes to avoid a pile of construction blocking bridge, and plunged 90 feet into a [[Mantaro River]], outskirt of [[Jauja]], [[Jun\u00edn Region]], Peru, killing 45 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* India 7 June \u2013 A bus plunged 100-feet into a ravine at outskirt of [[Baramulla]], Jammu and Kashmir, India, killing fifty people and injuring twenty. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 24 June Brazil \u2013 Two vehicles of [[S\u00e3o Paulo]]-Rio Grande do Norte regular route buses tumbled down a 100-feet embankment at Outskirt of [[Estancia]], [[Sergipe]], Brazil, killing 31 people and injuring fifty. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 16 July Japan \u2013 A landslide caused by intense rain collapsed a tunnel, striking a minibus and killing 15 people at [[Echizen, Fukui|Echizen]], [[Fukui Prefecture]], Japan.<ref name=\"natpoljap\"/>\n* 21 September United States - [[Alton, Texas bus crash]] - A truck hit a school bus in [[Alton, Texas]], and the bus fell into a caliche pit filled with water; 21 students died.<ref name=Fischler>{{cite news|author=Fischler, Jacob|url=https://www.themonitor.com/news/local/article_1b51b760-4140-11e4-9f7b-0017a43b2370.html|title=Remembering the 21: Sunday is 25th anniversary of Alton bus tragedy |newspaper=[[The Monitor (Texas)|The Monitor]]|date=21 September 2014|accessdate=2 August 2018}}</ref>\n* 8 October Canada \u2013 [[1989 Cormier-Village hayride accident|Cormier-Village Hayride Accident]], 13 adults and children are killed and 30 are injured near [[Shediac|Shediac, New Brunswick]], when a transport truck carrying logs spilled its cargo while passing a loaded hayride.\n* 20 October Australia \u2013 [[Grafton bus crash|The Grafton bus crash]] \u2013 A [[Sydney]]-[[Brisbane]] Sunliner Coaches tourist bus collided head-on with a tractor trailer truck near [[Grafton, New South Wales]], Australia, killing 21 people and injuring 22.\n* 22 December Australia \u2013 35 people are killed in the [[Kempsey bus crash]] on the [[Pacific Highway (Australia)|Pacific Highway]] near [[Kempsey, New South Wales]].\n* 24 December \u2013 A regular route bus plunged into a procession at Nag-el-Hobeiki, [[Luxor]], Egypt, killing 13 people and injuring 8. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\n==1990s==\n\n===1990===\n* 26 January Ireland. Eight people were killed, and five more were injured, when a tree crashed onto a mini bus during the Burns Day storm. It was the worst incident of a storm that killed 97 people across Western Europe and the British Isles.\n* 28 February Malaysia \u2013 17 people including 11 [[Federal Reserve Unit]] (FRU) riot police personal were killed in a [[1990 Kuala Lumpur\u2013Karak Highway crash|collision]] between FRU riot police vehicles, [[tanker lorry]], [[bus|passenger bus]] and 10 [[Automobile|cars]] on the [[Kuala Lumpur\u2013Karak Expressway]], Malaysia.\n* 20 March United States \u2013 Whilst on tour, a semi trailer rammed into a [[sleeper bus|tour bus]] containing singer [[Gloria Estefan]], husband [[Emilio Estefan|Emilio]], their son and three other passengers at [[Tobyhanna, Pennsylvania]], severely injuring Gloria. Following extensive surgery, she returned to an international tour ten months after the crash.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Dougherty |first=Steve |url=http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20117308,00.html |title=Singer Gloria Estefan Takes Her First Steps to Recovery After a Frightening Bus Crash |magazine=People.com |date=9 April 1990 |accessdate=7 February 2013}}</ref>\n* 22 April Cuba \u2013 Two buses collide in [[Havana]], Cuba, killing 11 people and seriously injuring 13.<ref>Reuters \"[https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9C0CE3D81239F937A15757C0A966958260&sec=&pagewanted=print Bus Crash in Havana Kills 11]\" ''The New York Times'' 24 April 1990</ref>\n* 3 June France \u2013 [[Joigny coach crash]]: A [[Shropshire]] based [[double-decker bus|double-decker coach]] bus suffered a blowout of the front tyre on the autoroute [[A6 autoroute (France)|A6]] near [[Auxerre]] when it was 20&nbsp;mph in excess of the speed limit, causing the 76-seat coach to crash, killing 11 people and injuring 61 British tourists, all returning from [[Costa Brava]]. This resulted in a legal action against [[Avon Rubber]], manufacturer of the tyre of the crash coach, its driver and his employer; resulting in the longest legal case in France.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/staffordshire/3043132.stm | work=BBC News | title=Bus driver guilty of 1990 deaths | date=3 July 2003 | accessdate=8 May 2010}}</ref>\n* 8 July USSR \u2013 A bus ignores a barrier at a railroad crossing and collides with a passenger train near [[Petrozavodsk]], [[Karelia]], Russia, killing 27 people (34 according to unofficial sources) and injuring 24. The bus driver is injured slightly.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ptzbus.nm.ru/avariya.html|title=Petrozavodskiy Avtobus site (Russian)|publisher=|accessdate=1 October 2014}}</ref>\n* 20 September \u2013 A mini-van skidded on the slippery road rammed inter-city bus exceeded speed and plunged off the road, and another inter-city bus hit into disaster site with rescuers working at outskirt of [[Semarang]], [[Central Java]], Indonesia, killing 33 people and injuring 17. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 24 September \u2013 A truck carrying two unsecured 20,000-liter [[liquefied petroleum gas]] tanks overturned on [[New Phetchaburi Road]], downtown [[Bangkok]], Thailand. The explosions and resulting fires consumed 43 vehicles and many buildings in the area, killing 59 people and injuring 89.<ref>Manager, [http://www.manager.co.th/Crime/ViewNews.aspx?NewsID=9500000106460 \u0e23\u0e33\u0e25\u0e36\u0e01 17 \u0e1b\u0e35 \"\u0e23\u0e16\u0e41\u0e01\u0e4a\u0e2a\u0e23\u0e30\u0e40\u0e1a\u0e34\u0e14\" \u0e42\u0e28\u0e01\u0e19\u0e32\u0e0f\u0e01\u0e23\u0e23\u0e21\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e08\u0e14\u0e08\u0e33 (17th Anniversary of the \"Gas Truck Explosion\" Tragedy)], 10 September 2007. Retrieved on 24 April 2009.</ref>\n*26 July 1990 Canada \u2013 A [[British Columbia]] bus carrying a dance troop to the Okanagon Peach Festival was in a terrible crash through the Rogers Pass, British Columbia. Transport truck lost its steel load, which struck the dance troop charter, killing the driver instantly as well as many young dancers and adults. The bus driver drove the bus into the embankment of rock rather than over the side of a cliff, saving the remainder of the people on the bus.\n* 9 November Netherlands \u2013 Almost at the same spot and with the same cause of the [[List of road accidents#1972|August 25, 1972 crash]]: in sudden dense fog on highway A16 west of [[Breda]], several cars and trucks collide in a huge pile-up. 10 people die and 28 are injured.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zero-meridean.nl/ramp_sel.html#6nov90|title=6 november 1990: Kettingbotsing A16, Breda|publisher=|accessdate=1 October 2014}}</ref>\n* 22 November USSR \u2013 A bus ignores a red light and collides with a train at a railroad crossing in [[Donetsk]], Ukraine, killing 19 people and wounding 13, though the bus driver is not injured.\n* 11 December United States \u2013 A 99 car pile-up due to fog on [[Interstate 75]] near [[Calhoun, Tennessee]] results in 12 deaths and 42 injured.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ntsb.gov/publictn/1992/HAR9202.htm|title=HIGHWAY ACCIDENT REPORT HAR-92-2|publisher=|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref>\n* 30 December USSR \u2013 56 people die in a collision involving a bus, truck and car on a highway between [[Voronezh]] and [[Rostov-on-Don]] in southwestern Russia.{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\n===1991===\n* 6 January Kenya \u2013 A bus slammed into a tree on a railroad crossing at outskirt of [[Murang'a]], [[Central Province (Kenya)|Central Province]], Kenya, in an incident caused by driver  losing control and excessive speed, killing 47 people, another 40 are injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 13 January \u2013 A [[Dapitan City|Dapitan]]-[[Dipolog City|Dipolog]] regular route bus plunged into a river at outskirt of [[Sindangan, Zamboanga del Norte|Sindangan]], [[Zamboanga del Norte]], Philippines, killing 25 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 15 February \u2013 A trailer truck carrying dynamite explodes at [[Thung Maphrao]], [[Phang Nga]], Thailand killing 171 local villagers.<ref>New York Times [https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9D0CE2DE173BF935A25751C0A967958260  'Dynamite Blast in Thailand Leaves 122 Onlookers Dead'] 16 February 1991, Retrieved 5 April 2006</ref>\n* 13 March UK \u2013 [[1991 M4 Motorway crash]]: 10 people die in a 45 vehicle pile up in foggy conditions on the M4 motorway near Hungerford.\n* 31 July United States \u2013 A bus carrying about 60 Girl Scouts overturns on a desert mountain road near [[California State Route 111|California Highway 111]] and not far from [[Palm Springs, California|Palm Springs]], killing 7 people.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9D0CE4DA123BF932A3575BC0A967958260 | work=The New York Times | title=7 Are Killed as Girl Scout Bus Overturns on Mountain Road | date=1 August 1991 | accessdate=8 May 2010}}</ref>\n* 4 August Zimbabwe \u2013 [[Nyanga bus accident]]: A crowded bus carrying school children from Regina Coeli Mission in Nyanga loses control and crashes in [[Troutbeck, Manicaland]], Zimbabwe, killing 91 people, including 82 children.\n* 7 August Austria \u2013 The brakes of a Hungarian tourist bus fail in [[Styria]], killing 15 people and injuring 28.<ref name=\"ADAC\" />\n* 29 November United States \u2013 [[1991 Interstate 5 dust storm]]: A dust storm on [[Interstate 5]] near [[Coalinga, California]] triggers a 164-vehicle pile up that leaves 17 people dead and 150 injured.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F2061FFC3A590C728CDDAB0994D9494D81|title=Scenes of Disaster in Pileup That Killed 17 in California|date=1 December 1991|publisher=|accessdate=15 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.on-this-day.com/onthisday/thedays/alldays/nov29.htm|title=On-This-Day.com: November 29|publisher=|accessdate=1 October 2014}}</ref>\n* 6 December Spain \u2013 A 25-vehicle pile-up crash due to dense fog on [[Autov\u00eda A-8]] near [[Amorebieta-Etxano]], [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Basque Country]] kills 17 people and injures 50. A spark sets the pile of cars afire.\n\n===1992===\n* 1 March Bangladesh \u2013 A regular route bus with 100 passengers vaulted into a road side creek at outskirt of [[Jaldhalca]], [[Nilphamari District]], Bangladesh, killing 25 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 3 April \u2013 A regular route bus with eighty passengers exploded and caught fire, and passengers jumping from out of window, because of broke open a door at outskirt of [[Yiyang]], [[Hunan]], China, killing 55 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 12 April South Africa \u2013 A bus carrying seventy school children ripped apart, after crashing into [[Buffalo River (KwaZulu-Natal)|Buffalo River]] bridge, [[Dundee, KwaZulu Natal]], South Africa, killing 33 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 18 April Argentina \u2013 A [[Buenos Aires]]-[[Mar del Plata]] regular route bus smashed with three vehicles amid foggy conditions at the outskirts of Mar del Plata, Argentina, killing 32 people and injuring 40.\n* 19 August \u2013 A bus falls down an embankment on the [[Autopista AP-7|A7]] highway in Spain, killing 45 and injuring 11.<ref>Associated Press \"[https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9E0CE7D7123DF933A1575BC0A964958260&sec=&pagewanted=print Bus Crash in Spain Kills 45]\" ''The New York Times'' 20 August 1992</ref>\n* 6 September Germany \u2013 Near [[Donaueschingen]] in the [[Black Forest]], a bus collides into a passenger car and is slit open by a [[crash barrier]]. 21 people die, 32 are injured seriously.<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite web|url=http://www.adac.de/Tests/Mobilitaet_und_Reise/Busreisen/bustest_2004/busunfaelle_europa/default.asp|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130210171452/http://www.adac.de/Tests/Mobilitaet_und_Reise/Busreisen/bustest_2004/busunfaelle_europa/default.asp|url-status=dead|archive-date=10 February 2013|title=Busunf\u00e4lle in Europa seit 1982|author=ADAC|accessdate=1 October 2014}}</ref>\n* 27 September Nepal \u2013 A truck plunged 450 feet below at outskirt of [[Dhankuta]], Nepal, killing 21 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 27 September Hungary \u2013 A minibus carrying German travellers collided with local train crossing at [[Ag\u00e1rd]], Hungary, killing 16 people, another three are injured. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 9 October Brazil \u2013 A bus carrying October Revelers entertainment group drove off a mountain road and plunged down cliff at outskirt of Sao Luis do Puruna, [[Paran\u00e1 (state)|Parana]], Brazil, killing 34 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\n===1993===\n* 9 January Argentina \u2013 Three buses collide and ignite on a highway in [[Santo Tom\u00e9, Corrientes]], Argentina, killing 55 people and injuring 70.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9F0CE7D6123CF932A25752C0A965958260|title=New York Times report|date=11 January 1993|publisher=|accessdate=15 November 2014}}</ref>\n* 7 April \u2013 At least 29 people were killed and 18 injured when a Turkish coach fell from a bridge into the Yantra River near Byala, after colliding with a lorry. Another heavy Turkish lorry slammed into a crane set up on the bridge to lift the wreckage out of the water.<ref>{{cite web|author=Custom byline text:&nbsp; From the archive |url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/sport/spl/aberdeen/29-die-in-bulgaria-s-worst-bus-crash-1.764864 |title=29 die in Bulgaria's worst bus crash |publisher=Herald Scotland |date=8 April 1993 |accessdate=1 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.apnewsarchive.com/1993/33-Killed-in-Bus-Accident/id-97efaf7a9a6698bac1676aa5c6062cfa |title=33 Killed in Bus Accident |publisher=Apnewsarchive.com |date=7 April 1993 |accessdate=1 April 2013}}</ref>\n* 30 April \u2013 A passenger train hit a bus carrying children of Shergli Primary schools at unguarded railroad crossing at [[Phutthamonthon]], [[Nakorn Pathom]], Thailand, killing 36 people, including 28 children. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 13 May Russia \u2013 A Sogratl-[[Makhachkala]] regular route bus plunged into 260-feet george at outskirt of [[Gunib]], [[Caucasus Mountains]] area, [[Dagestan]], Russia, killing 25 people. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 27 May Peru \u2013 A bus carrying Santiago de Chocorvos Conference business owners plunged 160-feet from road near foothill at outskirt of [[Ica (city)|Ica]], Peru, in an incident caused by mechanical failure, killing 21 people and injuring eleven. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 24 July Indonesia \u2013 A [[Surabaya]]-Pandanwangi passenger train rammed into an intercity bus an unguarded railroad crossing, and a bus dragged for eighty-yard before the train halted at [[Jombang Regency|Jombang]], [[West Java]], Indonesia, killing fifteen people and injuring twenty. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 3 October Kenya \u2013 A multiple road disaster, including a passenger bus, truck and many vehicles are crashed at Nakuru-[[Eldoret]] road, [[Nakuru]], Kenya, killing 35 people and injuring 41. {{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n* 10 November \u2013 A fiery pile-up on autoroute [[A10 autoroute (France)|A10]] near [[Mirambeau, Charente-Maritime|Mirambeau]], France leaves 15 people dead and 53 injured.<ref>[http://www.lemonde.fr/cgi-bin/ACHATS/acheter.cgi?offre=ARCHIVES&type_item=ART_ARCH_30J&objet_id=738143&clef=ARC-TRK-G_01 Carambolage de Mirambeau: 17 automobilistes et 2 routiers  jug\u00e9s pour homicides involontaires], 23 J